research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0011.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A thresholded sparse activation family may beat the current hybrid mainline by learning which latent logits should be suppressed before top-k selection rather than only reshaping logits with extra branches. Test jumprelu at K=128 with Adam as a fresh quality-first family probe.","summary":"The latest hybrid_topk edit was a normal-runtime regression, and several rounds have now been spent on local hybrid stabilization without another gain. This round shifts back to architecture exploration with an untried family whose learned thresholds could improve selectivity at the same K=128 anchor point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a deliberate reset to a genuinely different sparse activation mechanism after the hybrid local edits stalled. The risk is that JumpReLU may proxy poorly under the fixed-K implementation, but it is the cleanest untried family with a credible path to lower FVU.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The best current full frontier remains hybrid_topk with Adam at K=128, expansion_factor=8, FVU 0.16189537942409515.","Round 11 reopens architecture exploration after hybrid local edits stalled, using jumprelu as a new family with learned thresholding at fixed K=128."],"next_hypotheses":["If jumprelu shows a strong proxy signal, promote it to full before doing more hybrid tuning.","If jumprelu is flat or worse, keep hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 as mainline and then decide between a new encoder family or a training-dynamics experiment on the hybrid checkpoint."]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0013.json:22:    "expected_win": "lower_fvu",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0020.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery and policy both point to a narrow param-only move: keep the current best working proxy configuration in hybrid_topk fixed and test whether it remains viable when K is reduced from 128 to 64. This is the required first step in K exploration, and it isolates the effect of sparsity level without confounding architecture or optimizer changes.","summary":"Run a proxy K=64 check on the current best working hybrid_topk configuration, holding the rest of the known-stable proxy settings fixed so this round cleanly measures the first smaller-K point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the runtime constraints exactly: no code edits, one coherent hypothesis, proxy-first, and explicit K exploration after recent crashes. I am using the best working proxy anchor rather than introducing any new family or secondary tuning, so the result should be interpretable even if K=64 regresses.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"false"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 20 obeys crash-recovery mode and performs a param-only K exploration run on the best working hybrid_topk proxy setup.","The first required smaller-K probe is K=64, with the rest of the stable hybrid_topk proxy configuration held fixed for interpretability.","This round is intended as the first step before a likely K=32 follow-up, unless K=64 shows an unexpected stability or quality failure that changes the plan."],"next_hypotheses":["If hybrid_topk at K=64 is stable and reasonably competitive, run the same configuration at K=32 next to complete the required smaller-K sweep.","If K=64 collapses badly or becomes unstable, keep the architecture fixed and consider a minor recovery adjustment within hybrid_topk rather than introducing a new family immediately."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:22:    "expected_win": "explore_unknown",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0016.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent hybrid and adaptive-threshold results suggest the main failure mode is not lack of an anchor but how nonlinear information is injected into support selection. A union_topk encoder that keeps the baseline linear top-k proposal intact while letting a nonlinear branch propose an alternate candidate set, with final support chosen from the union rather than from perturbed logits, could lower FVU by adding complementary features without destabilizing the proven linear path.","summary":"The orthogonality regularization follow-up regressed on both proxy FVU and throughput, so more local regularization sweeps are not justified. This round adds a new `union_topk` family under `sparsify/` and tests it first at the same K=128/ef=8/Adam anchor, probing whether branch-level candidate union is a better way to add encoder expressivity than the recent additive, gating, or suppression mechanisms.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"union_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single coherent architecture bet that directly addresses the weakness exposed by recent edits: nonlinear branches have either interfered with or failed to improve baseline support. The risk is that merged candidate sets may still be too redundant to beat hybrid_topk, but the design preserves the strongest prior while giving the nonlinear branch a cleaner path to help.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"union_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/union_topk_sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/__init__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 16 adds a new union_topk family that preserves the linear TopK proposal and lets a nonlinear branch contribute only through alternate candidate proposals before the final global top-k.","A quick local import and forward check passed for union_topk before returning control to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If union_topk shows a strong proxy gain, promote it to full as the next mainline quality candidate.","If union_topk is flat or weak, the next round should either stabilize this branch-union family with a family-specific width change or pivot to a more radical new encoder design rather than returning to recent discarded regularization ideas."]}
