research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0013.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A gated SAE may materially lower proxy FVU at K=128 by decoupling support selection from coefficient magnitude, letting one branch learn which features should fire while another learns how strongly they should reconstruct. After two flat jumprelu stabilization rounds and stalled hybrid local search, this is the cleanest untried quality-first family already supported by the execution layer.","summary":"JumpReLU did not produce a meaningful stabilization gain, and recent local tuning around the current hybrid mainline has not closed the quality gap. This round shifts to a new existing architecture family with a distinct encoder bias: independent gating and magnitude branches at the same K=128/ef=8/Adam anchor, evaluated first as a proxy quality probe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single coherent family exploration, not another weak local sweep. The main risk is that sigmoid-gated selection could saturate and undertrain, but the architectural change is clean, already implemented, and directly targets support quality rather than cost.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 13 opens the previously untested gated family as a quality-first K=128 proxy probe after jumprelu threshold tuning remained flat around 0.275 proxy FVU.","The gated architecture decouples latent support selection from activation magnitude, which is a substantively different encoder bias from hybrid additive correction and jumprelu thresholding."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated shows a strong proxy signal, promote it to full before returning to smaller-K or cost work.","If gated is also weak, bias the next round toward another genuinely different encoder family or a code edit for a new architecture rather than more parameter-only tuning on recent families."]}
