research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The stabilized factorized_topk crash was caused by an implementation bug in the widened hidden-path projection, not by the architecture itself. Fix the hidden-to-latent projection and rerun the same K=128 factorized_topk stabilization pass to recover a valid quality signal.","summary":"Round 5 produced a shape-mismatch crash inside factorized_topk after the widening edit, so the next move is a direct bug-fix rerun rather than abandoning the family. This keeps the hypothesis narrow: validate the intended wider gated factorized encoder before making any new architectural decision.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the correct response to the last round because the failure was a concrete code bug, not a training-quality outcome. The rerun is still only worth one more round; if the fixed version remains poor, this branch should be deprioritized.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/factorized_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 5 factorized_topk crashed due to a hidden-to-latent shape mismatch in the widened encoder path, so that result should not be treated as architectural evidence.","Round 6 fixes factorized_topk by adding an explicit hidden-to-latent projection and excluding the unused base encoder from optimization before re-running the same stabilization test."],"next_hypotheses":["If the fixed factorized_topk now yields a valid proxy improvement, keep incubating the family with quality-focused tuning.","If the fixed factorized_topk still performs poorly under normal runtime, stop spending rounds on current built-in families and move to a genuinely new encoder design."]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0019.json:22:    "expected_win": "lower_fvu",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0010.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"hybrid_topk may now be limited by using the nonlinear branch only as an additive correction; letting it multiplicatively modulate the linear logits should improve support shaping while preserving the strong baseline path. Re-test hybrid_topk at the best-known K=128, expansion_factor=8, optimizer=adam setting after this targeted hybrid-family stabilization edit.","summary":"The expansion_factor=16 follow-up did not improve full FVU and cost substantial throughput, so the next move should be a targeted architecture refinement rather than more brute-force scaling. This round keeps the winning hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 setup and upgrades the nonlinear branch to modulate linear logits as well as add residual logits.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a narrow, defensible follow-up on the current best family and it directly addresses the likely limit of the present hybrid design without reopening the broader search space. It still adds encoder complexity, so any quality gain will need later cost scrutiny against the ef=8 Adam mainline.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/hybrid_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["hybrid_topk with Adam and expansion_factor=16 achieved better proxy FVU but slightly worse full FVU (0.1623645443469286 vs 0.16189537942409515) and a clear throughput regression, so brute-force scaling is not the next priority.","Round 10 stabilizes hybrid_topk by adding a zero-initialized multiplicative modulation path on top of the existing additive nonlinear residual, keeping the model anchored to the proven linear encoder at initialization."],"next_hypotheses":["If the modulated hybrid_topk improves proxy FVU, promote it to full as the next mainline quality candidate.","If the modulated hybrid_topk is flat or worse, keep the current hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 checkpoint as mainline and revisit training dynamics or a genuinely new family instead of more local hybrid edits."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0001.json:71:    "expected_win": "explore_unknown",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0017.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The union_topk prototype likely failed because its nonlinear branch proposed candidates from the same centered input as the linear branch, so it mostly duplicated baseline support. Conditioning the nonlinear proposer on the linear branch residual, widening that branch, and letting it over-propose candidates before the final global top-k should increase support complementarity at K=128 and lower proxy FVU.","summary":"Stabilize the new union_topk family with a complementary-proposal encoder: the linear path still anchors selection, but the nonlinear branch now reads the linear residual and can surface extra candidates that the baseline top-k misses. This is a single quality-first proxy follow-up on the most recent new family, rather than another local sweep on hybrid_topk.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"union_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays within one coherent family hypothesis and directly targets the main weakness of the round-16 prototype: redundant candidate proposals. The main risk is that proxy training may still be too short for the wider residual-conditioned branch to separate from the linear anchor, but this is a more informative family-specific follow-up than pivoting away after one near-baseline prototype.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"union_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/union_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 17 stabilizes union_topk by making the nonlinear proposal branch residual-conditioned on the linear partial reconstruction instead of reading the same centered input.","The union_topk stabilization also widens the nonlinear branch and lets it over-propose 2k candidates before the final global top-k, aiming to improve candidate diversity without changing decode semantics.","A local import/forward/backward sanity check passed for the edited union_topk implementation before handing control back to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If residual-conditioned union_topk materially improves proxy FVU, promote this family toward mainline comparison and consider a full run.","If it remains near the recent 0.275 proxy plateau under normal runtime, pivot away from branch-union variants to a more radical encoder family rather than spending more rounds on local union_topk tuning."]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0015.json:22:    "expected_win": "lower_fvu",
research/history_archive/history_20260320_152535/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At fixed K=128, a Hadamard-rotated residual_topk SAE will beat the rotated topk proxy anchor on FVU by letting a second encoder pass allocate support on the first-pass reconstruction residual, reducing one-shot top-k competition without changing the execution layer.","summary":"Add a new residual_topk prototype under sparsify/ and run it at K=128 with Hadamard and the baseline signum optimizer. This is a quality-first architecture exploration step after routed_group_topk produced a clearly weak proxy result under normal runtime, so the next move is a new family rather than another local sweep.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"residual_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows research/program.md: one coherent hypothesis, proxy by default, and architecture exploration after several non-improving rounds. The implementation is narrowly scoped under sparsify/ and passed a local instantiation plus forward/backward sanity check. The main risk is that splitting support across two passes could underuse the shared dictionary or create duplicate selections, so a weak proxy result would argue against this family rather than against residual-style search in general.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/__init__.py","sparsify/residual_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Read research/program.md before deciding; with repeated non-improvements and a normal-health but weak routed_group_topk result, this round should explore a new quality-first family rather than another narrow sweep.","No operator_hints were present in the structured context for this round.","Added a residual_topk prototype that runs a second top-k encoder pass on the first-branch residual and then selects the final K latents from the union of both branches' candidates.","Local sanity check passed for residual_topk: Python instantiation plus forward/backward succeeded on a toy tensor, so the family is compatible with the existing SparseCoder training path."],"next_hypotheses":["If residual_topk shows promising proxy FVU, keep the family alive with a stabilization pass over optimizer or orthogonality regularization before considering any smaller-K search.","If residual_topk improves quality but shows throughput regressions, follow with a performance-focused pass instead of discarding the architecture.","If residual_topk is clearly weak on proxy FVU, move on to another encoder family such as a factorized or wider multi-branch routed encoder rather than spending more rounds on local tuning."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0012.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"jumprelu looks promising enough to deserve a family-specific stabilization pass, and its current default threshold initialization is likely too weak to realize the benefit of learned gating. Test jumprelu at K=128 with Adam using a higher initial threshold and smoother STE bandwidth so the encoder starts from a more selective regime.","summary":"The first jumprelu proxy was slightly better than the recent hybrid proxy points, but not strong enough to justify an immediate full run. This round keeps the new family and optimizer fixed and tunes its threshold dynamics directly, which is the most important family-specific lever for quality.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the right follow-up because JumpReLU's distinctive mechanism is its learned thresholding, so the defaults deserve at least one targeted pass before judging the family. The chosen threshold and bandwidth may still be off, but the hypothesis is clean and easy to evaluate.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.01"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.01"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["jumprelu at K=128/ef8/adam reached proxy FVU 0.2749013416469097, which is modestly competitive with recent hybrid proxy points but not yet enough for promotion.","Round 12 performs the first family-specific jumprelu stabilization pass by increasing the initial threshold and STE bandwidth to encourage more meaningful learned gating."],"next_hypotheses":["If stabilized jumprelu materially improves proxy FVU, promote it to full before spending more rounds on hybrid variants.","If stabilized jumprelu is flat or worse, keep hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 as mainline and either try another new family or return to a training-dynamics experiment on the hybrid checkpoint."]}
