research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0015.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent new families have all clustered far above the current hybrid full frontier, so the most credible next move is a training-dynamics pass on the one family that has actually improved full FVU. Adding a modest orthogonality penalty to hybrid_topk may reduce decoder interference between active features, sharpen the effective support at K=128, and improve reconstruction quality without changing the proven architecture.","summary":"Adaptive-threshold TopK matched the jumprelu-level proxy plateau rather than breaking through, so architecture exploration has not yet produced a stronger mainline candidate. This round returns to the best-known hybrid_topk K=128/ef=8/Adam setup and tests a single quality-focused regularization change, using proxy first to see whether reduced decoder interference can move FVU meaningfully below the recent 0.27 proxy band.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a narrow follow-up on the only family with a verified full win, not another broad sweep. The risk is that orthogonality regularization could trade away too much fitting capacity, but it is a clean way to test whether the remaining bottleneck is feature interference rather than encoder expressivity.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"ORTHO_LAMBDA","value":"1e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Adaptive_threshold_topk did not improve beyond the recent jumprelu-level proxy plateau, so support-suppression alone is not enough to beat the current hybrid mainline.","Round 15 returns to hybrid_topk for a training-dynamics probe, testing whether mild decoder orthogonality regularization can improve K=128 quality by reducing active-feature interference."],"next_hypotheses":["If hybrid_topk with ortho regularization improves proxy FVU materially, promote it to full as the next mainline quality test.","If the ortho pass is flat or worse, bias the next round toward a more expressive new architecture edit rather than more local regularization sweeps."]}
research/history_archive/history_20260320_152535/logs/agent_action_0009.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At fixed K=128, a Hadamard-rotated mixture_topk SAE with a softly routed two-expert encoder will lower proxy FVU versus the current linear top-k anchor by letting different encoder experts specialize to different token regimes without the hard capacity bottlenecks and optimization friction seen in grouped routing variants.","summary":"Add a new mixture_topk prototype under sparsify/ and run it as a proxy at K=128 with Hadamard and the baseline signum optimizer. This is a quality-first architecture exploration step after factorized_topk produced a clearly weak proxy result, so the next move is a smoother higher-expressivity encoder family rather than another local sweep.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"mixture_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps to one coherent hypothesis, stays within sparsify/, and preserves the fixed execution layer. The new family is intentionally minimal: two soft-routed encoder experts feeding the standard fixed-K decoder path. A local instantiation plus forward/backward sanity check passed. The main risk is that soft expert averaging may collapse toward a single branch under signum, so a weak proxy result would argue for either optimizer-specific stabilization or moving on quickly.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"mixture_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/__init__.py","sparsify/mixture_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Read research/program.md before deciding; with factorized_topk clearly weak under normal runtime, this round should try a new quality-first encoder family rather than continue narrow local tuning.","No operator_hints were present in the structured context for this round.","Added a mixture_topk prototype that uses a soft two-expert encoder mixture before the standard fixed-K top-k selection, aiming to increase routing expressivity without hard group-capacity limits.","Local sanity check passed for mixture_topk: Python instantiation plus forward/backward succeeded on a toy tensor, so the family is compatible with the existing SparseCoder training path."],"next_hypotheses":["If mixture_topk shows promising proxy FVU, keep the family alive with a stabilization pass over optimizer or family-specific expert count/routing sharpness before considering any smaller-K search.","If mixture_topk improves quality but shows a throughput regression, follow with an edit_perf_code pass focused on the extra expert projection path instead of discarding the family.","If mixture_topk is clearly weak on proxy FVU, move on to another higher-expressivity encoder family rather than spending more rounds on local tuning around top-k."]}
