research/history_archive/history_20260320_152535/logs/agent_action_0004.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At fixed K=128, a Hadamard-rotated routed-group TopK SAE with a differentiable coarse router and Adam optimization will beat the rotated topk proxy anchor on FVU by reducing cross-feature competition before exact latent top-k selection, while avoiding the hard-router failure mode that made plain group_topk unattractive.","summary":"Run a proxy prototype for a rotated routed_group_topk family at K=128, using moderate group capacity and Adam so the straight-through router can actually learn. This is a quality-first architecture exploration step that leverages an already-implemented differentiable routing family in sparsify/ instead of spending another round on weak local tuning around topk or on the poorly-performing gated prototype.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"rotated_routed_group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows research/program.md: proxy by default, one coherent hypothesis, and quality-first architecture exploration after two non-improving rounds. It also corrects a stale assumption in memory: the repo already contains routed_group_topk with differentiable routing, so this is a cleaner grouped-routing test than hard group_topk. The main risks are router hyperparameter sensitivity and over-restricting the candidate pool if active_groups is too small; using Adam and a moderate routed capacity is the most defensible first prototype.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_group_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3e-4"},{"key":"NUM_GROUPS","value":"32"},{"key":"ACTIVE_GROUPS","value":"8"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Read research/program.md before deciding; it again points toward proxy quality exploration rather than more weak local parameter search.","No operator_hints were present in structured context for this round.","The current sparsify codebase already implements routed_group_topk with a straight-through differentiable router, so the earlier belief that grouped routing is only hard/non-differentiable is outdated.","A routed grouped family is the next clean architecture bet because gated failed badly on proxy FVU and routed_group_topk can test coarse-to-fine support selection without requiring code edits."],"next_hypotheses":["If rotated routed_group_topk shows promising proxy FVU but unstable optimization, keep the family alive with a stabilization pass over num_groups, active_groups, and LR.","If rotated routed_group_topk improves quality but shows poor throughput, follow with an edit_perf_code pass rather than discarding the family.","If rotated routed_group_topk fails to show useful quality signal, escalate to a more novel encoder family such as a factorized or multi-branch routed encoder instead of returning to weak local topk tuning."]}
