research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:417:{"event_id": "evt_1774034073922657517", "ts": 1774034073, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 30, "session_id": "019d0ca2-ba0e-7ee1-8dd5-323cd7a840b3", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "routed", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0ca2-ba0e-7ee1-8dd5-323cd7a840b3", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "routed", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "quality", "hypothesis": "The routed family did not get a fair read because its initial support selection was too close to baseline top-k and tripped the identical-to-baseline guard. Making routed support depend on an independently initialized router with a direct, non-monotone routing bonus should produce a genuine architecture signal in proxy and reveal whether separate support selection can outperform the stalled gated search."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:424:{"event_id": "evt_1774034169414928802", "ts": 1774034169, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 31, "session_id": "019d0ca2-ba0e-7ee1-8dd5-323cd7a840b3", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "routed", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0ca2-ba0e-7ee1-8dd5-323cd7a840b3", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "routed", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "quality", "hypothesis": "Seven non-improving rounds indicate the current gated-centered search is fundamentally stalled, and the updated routed encoder is now the highest-value different architecture to test because it separates support selection from reconstruction magnitude without relying on the same gated monotone ranking. A clean proxy run of routed at K=128 under the best validated training regime can reveal whether this support-selection change opens a new quality path that top-k and gated did not."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:446:{"event_id": "evt_1774060313705784597", "ts": 1774060313, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 32, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "Severe stagnation and two non-competitive K=128 architecture probes suggest the current global-ranking support mechanisms are locally exhausted. A new `group_topk` prototype that enforces one local winner per small latent group before the global top-k may reduce redundant feature selection and improve reconstruction quality or cost under the same validated training regime."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:452:{"event_id": "evt_1774060395162709833", "ts": 1774060395, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 33, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "quality", "hypothesis": "After nine non-improving rounds and non-competitive K=128 results from topk and routed, the current global support-ranking direction looks structurally weak. The newly added `group_topk` family is the next fundamentally different architecture probe because it imposes local winner-take-all competition before global selection, which may improve feature diversity and reduce redundant support allocation under the same validated training regime."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:458:{"event_id": "evt_1774060442579187597", "ts": 1774060442, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 34, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "stability", "hypothesis": "In crash recovery mode, the safest informative move is to return to the best known working gated K=128 configuration and make the smallest remaining stabilization adjustment. A milder auxiliary pressure of AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 may preserve the strong gated baseline while avoiding the degradation seen at 0.0625, giving a cleaner read on whether the current anchor is slightly over-regularized."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:486:{"event_id": "evt_1774060953101577713", "ts": 1774060953, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 35, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "pareto", "hypothesis": "With the gated family now improved at K=128 via AUXK_ALPHA=0.01, the next clean move is to test whether that stronger regime transfers to a smaller sparsity budget and improves the Pareto frontier rather than only the anchor point. A gated K=64 proxy run under the same stabilized settings can reveal whether the current best family can materially outperform the old JumpReLU K=64 point."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:511:{"event_id": "evt_1774061358691159612", "ts": 1774061358, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 36, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "pareto", "hypothesis": "The stabilized gated regime has now improved both K=128 and K=64, so the next clean Pareto probe is to test whether that same family extends to K=32 and can displace the older JumpReLU low-K point. A gated K=32 proxy run under the same validated settings will show whether the current best family can dominate more of the frontier rather than remaining a high-K-only solution."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:537:{"event_id": "evt_1774061974833512932", "ts": 1774061974, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 37, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "pareto", "hypothesis": "Now that gated holds the full frontier at K=128, K=64, and K=32, the next informative move is to test whether the low-K regime is over-capacitated rather than quality-limited. Reducing gated expansion_factor from 16 to 8 at K=32 may preserve most of the newly won quality while improving cost signals and possibly sharpening feature competition enough to strengthen the Pareto tradeoff."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:568:{"event_id": "evt_1774067537606385185", "ts": 1774067537, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 40, "session_id": "019d0ea8-858b-7aa1-86fa-da53d5187980", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0ea8-858b-7aa1-86fa-da53d5187980", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "The best current working point is gated K=128 EF=16 with signum, LR=1.6e-3, and AUXK_ALPHA=0.01. Since lowering AUXK_ALPHA from 0.03125 to 0.01 materially improved both proxy and full FVU, the next lowest-risk recovery move is to remove the auxiliary penalty entirely. Testing AUXK_ALPHA=0 on the same gated K=128 anchor may further reduce reconstruction interference and improve FVU without introducing architectural or launch instability."}}
