research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1756:{"event_id": "evt_1774173763638305730", "ts": 1774173763, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 89, "session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "two_code_residual_vq", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "two_code_residual_vq", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "Single-code `residual_vq` is likely too coarse at `K=32, EF=12`, leaving too much residual burden for the sparse correction. A new `two_code_residual_vq` family that composes two hard codebook selections before the same sparse residual stage may recover a better low-K tradeoff by moving more structure into the discrete trunk without raising K or EF."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1763:{"event_id": "evt_1774174041001172148", "ts": 1774174041, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 90, "session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "With incubation slots saturated and recent fresh-family probes weak or blocked, the least-bad informative move is to return to the strongest existing alternative architecture at the active low-K target. `lowrank_residual` is the closest non-gated same-`(K=32, EF=12)` competitor seen so far, so rerunning that exact architecture point is the best available architecture-level comparison against the weak discrete branch and the slightly better gated local baseline."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1776:{"event_id": "evt_1774174236892721070", "ts": 1774174236, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 91, "session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "`lowrank_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` is now effectively tied with the best exact-neighborhood result, so the next informative move is to map this same non-gated family at the adjacent low-K point `K=40` before touching EF. If the family scales more favorably than `lowrank_gated_residual` across low K, `K=40, EF=12` is the cleanest same-family, same-EF check."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1789:{"event_id": "evt_1774174434591178451", "ts": 1774174434, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 92, "session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "routed", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "routed", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "Low-rank residual variants at `K=32` and `K=40` have now converged to near-parity with the local best without producing a real win, so the next informative move is to switch to a fundamentally different sparse-support mechanism at the same low-K comparison point. Running `routed` at `K=40, EF=12` tests whether explicit routing can improve the low-K tradeoff where both gated and non-gated residual magnitude families have stalled."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1802:{"event_id": "evt_1774174634331071929", "ts": 1774174634, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 93, "session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "two_code_residual_vq", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "two_code_residual_vq", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "Single-code `residual_vq` was clearly too coarse at low K, and both routed and residual-magnitude alternatives have now failed to improve the `K=40, EF=12` local frontier. A real `two_code_residual_vq` prototype that composes two hard codebook selections before the sparse residual stage is the next informative architecture move because it strengthens the discrete trunk without raising K or EF."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1832:{"event_id": "evt_1774175472305207508", "ts": 1774175472, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 94, "session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "batch_topk", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "batch_topk", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "architecture_signal", "hypothesis": "The current low-K stall suggests the main failure mode may be fixed per-sample top-k allocation rather than trunk capacity alone. Running `batch_topk` at the exact active comparison point `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe is the cleanest fundamentally different architecture test because it changes the sparsity mechanism itself while keeping the same low-K lane and same EF band."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1845:{"event_id": "evt_1774175672952665524", "ts": 1774175672, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 95, "session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d14ea-730e-75e1-9200-ca4cb6c1e330", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "architecture_signal", "hypothesis": "`batch_topk` at the exact active point `K=40, EF=12` was decisively weak, so the next informative move is another fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than more residual-family or discrete-trunk tuning. Running `jumprelu` at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe tests whether smoother thresholded support selection recovers low-K quality where routing, residual-VQ, two-code residual-VQ, and batch-budget allocation all failed."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1859:{"event_id": "evt_1774175950327110351", "ts": 1774175950, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 96, "session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "whitened_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "whitened_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "The exact active point `(K=40, EF=12)` has now rejected several alternative sparsity mechanisms, while the strongest same-`(K,EF)` signal remains `lowrank_residual`. A space-first follow-up is more justified than more threshold/routing tweaks: adding residual whitening/preconditioning to the proven low-rank trunk may make the residual easier to sparsify at low K and lower proxy FVU without relying on EF>16."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1866:{"event_id": "evt_1774176218806722715", "ts": 1774176218, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 97, "session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "whitened_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "whitened_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "The exact active point `(K=40, EF=12)` has rejected multiple alternative sparsity mechanisms, while `lowrank_residual` remains the strongest same-neighborhood baseline. The new `whitened_lowrank_residual` family was added specifically to test whether residual preconditioning, rather than another sparsity-rule swap, can improve low-K quality at the same `(K, EF)`, so the next informative move is to execute that unchanged proxy comparison before branching further."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1879:{"event_id": "evt_1774176439801197587", "ts": 1774176439, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 98, "session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "two_code_residual_vq", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "two_code_residual_vq", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "The exact active point `(K=40, EF=12)` has now rejected several fundamentally different mechanisms, and the one non-TopK family with the best remaining same-EF low-K signal is `two_code_residual_vq`. Since lower K is the top priority and `K=32, EF=12` is still sparsely explored outside the residual baseline, the next informative move is to map this discrete coarse-plus-residual family down to `K=32` before spending another round on EF or another new local tweak."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1892:{"event_id": "evt_1774176644293639694", "ts": 1774176644, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 99, "session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "The low-K lane has now rejected several support-selection tweaks and discrete residual variants, which suggests the failure mode may be a single global dictionary trying to cover heterogeneous samples rather than the exact sparse mechanism alone. A new `bucketed_lowrank_residual` family that keeps the proven low-rank trunk but routes samples between two residual dictionaries by activation norm can test a stronger problem reformulation at the active target `K=32, EF=12` without increasing K or EF."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1899:{"event_id": "evt_1774176915766062047", "ts": 1774176915, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 100, "session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "The low-K lane has repeatedly rejected support-selection tweaks, whitening variants, and discrete residual families, so the strongest pending informative move is to execute the newly added `bucketed_lowrank_residual` reformulation at the exact active target. Conditioning the residual dictionary on coarse sample regime may recover useful low-K capacity where single-dictionary residual models and other mechanism swaps have stalled, without changing K or EF."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1911:{"event_id": "evt_1774177085919871002", "ts": 1774177085, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 101, "session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "run_stability", "hypothesis": "`bucketed_lowrank_residual` did not fail on quality; it failed on a narrow implementation blocker because the architecture string was not registered in config validation and/or factory dispatch. The correct next move is a repair-only follow-up that wires the existing family into the `sparsify/` registration path and reruns the exact same `K=32, EF=12` proxy target unchanged."}}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/timeline.jsonl:1957:{"event_id": "evt_1774178195448039745", "ts": 1774178195, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 102, "session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d151e-f057-7ab3-a1e7-776eaf5fbf59", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "bucketed_lowrank_residual", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "`bucketed_lowrank_residual` produced the strongest exact-neighborhood result seen so far at `K=32, EF=12`, so the next informative move is to keep the family fixed and map it to the adjacent low-K point `K=40` before any EF work. This preserves same-EF fairness, prioritizes K-lane coverage, and tests whether the conditional residual-dictionary reformulation remains competitive beyond a single low-K point."}}
