research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0085.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After repeated weak low-K results from `batch_topk`, `routed`, `two_stage_residual`, and `lowrank_residual`, the next informative move is a simpler discrete residual architecture that drops the failed `residual_vq_topk` registration path and tests whether coarse codebook reconstruction plus residual correction is a better low-K framing. Implement a new `residual_vq` family and run it at `K=32, EF=12` with the shared stable recipe.","summary":"Add a fresh `residual_vq` prototype under `sparsify/` and launch a proxy comparison at `K=32, EF=12` using the unchanged mainline optimizer/LR recipe. This is a fundamentally different low-K direction, stays in the preferred EF band, and avoids more retuning on families that already look weak.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Obtain a first clean low-K signal from a non-TopK discrete residual family that may outperform the recent weak routing and batch-allocation pivots.","family_name":"residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a real architecture pivot, not another local tweak. It also reduces complexity relative to the failed `residual_vq_topk` branch by removing the extra TopK coupling that never reached a valid run.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"residual_vq","K":"32","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/residual_vq.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 84: `residual_vq_topk` remains an implementation-blocked branch after repeated registration failures and should be treated as archived unless a brand-new concrete repair hypothesis appears.","Round 83: `batch_topk` at `K=32, EF=12` was clearly weak (`FVU 0.42549`) and should no longer consume mainline low-K budget.","Meta-analysis warning applies: too many incubating families; stale weak branches should be archived as new architecture work proceeds."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq` at `K=32, EF=12` runs cleanly and is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `residual_vq` runs cleanly but is still weak, pivot next to an input-space or output-aware architecture change rather than another sparse-allocation variant.","If `residual_vq` fails with a concrete implementation error, do one narrow repair-focused follow-up on the same target before judging the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0034.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Nine no-improve rounds indicate the current search direction around lowrank_gated_residual is exhausted, and the latest architecture pivot to `jumprelu` remained clearly uncompetitive even under the strongest shared recipe. The least-bad next informative move is to switch the single primary variable to a different existing architecture mechanism with real prior signal: rerun `two_stage_residual` at K=128 under the current strongest stable recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`) to test whether hierarchical residual allocation benefits from the stronger modern training regime.","summary":"Run a proxy comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual` at K=128 using the current strong shared training recipe, changing only architecture. This is a fundamentally different sparse-mechanism probe after both lowrank_gated_residual tuning and the refreshed `jumprelu` comparison failed to improve the frontier.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This round follows the mandatory architecture pivot and avoids another minor lowrank_gated_residual tweak after repeated stagnation. It also stays on an already implemented, previously working family with some real full-signal evidence, which is lower risk than opening a brand-new code path immediately after multiple failed directions.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After the refreshed `jumprelu` probe stayed far behind, the next architecture pivot moves to `two_stage_residual` rather than returning to lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning.","`two_stage_residual` is chosen because it is a genuinely different hierarchical sparse-allocation mechanism with prior working evidence, but it has not yet been re-tested under the strongest current shared recipe.","This round isolates architecture only and checks whether residual reconstruction staged across two passes can recover quality that single-pass alternatives are missing at the K=128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` is competitive at K=128 proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `two_stage_residual` remains clearly behind, archive it as a current mainline challenger and plan the next round around a new architecture mechanism rather than more local sweeps.","If `two_stage_residual` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code fix instead of discarding the family on architecture grounds."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0068.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Eighteen straight no-improve rounds mean the recent EF=8 recovery ladder is no longer the right mainline. The least-risk stagnation break is a same-band architecture comparison in the preferred EF=16 regime: run `lowrank_residual` at `K=48` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to test whether the simpler ungated low-rank residual encoder gives a better lower-K quality/cost tradeoff than the recent gated-recovery path.","summary":"Shift from the exhausted EF=8 recovery sweep to a fairer architecture comparison in the allowed main band. Probe `lowrank_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=16` in proxy, holding optimizer and LR fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This satisfies the stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than doing another minor tweak. The main risk is that `K=48` is an interpolated point for `lowrank_residual`, so the read may still be mostly frontier-mapping rather than a direct win, but it is a cleaner informative move than more EF=8 recovery rounds.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"48"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Break the EF=8 recovery loop after 18 no-improve rounds; return to same-EF architecture comparison in the preferred EF=12/16 band.","Use `K=48` as the lower-K comparison point so the round still prioritizes Pareto expansion while switching the primary variable back to architecture."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is competitive, continue the same family downward to `K=40` before reopening optimizer sweeps.","If `lowrank_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is clearly weak, pivot to another fundamentally different existing family in the same `EF=16` band rather than returning to more `lowrank_gated_residual` recovery tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0020.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improved the full K=64 frontier, so the next clean stabilization move is to test whether the same added residual capacity also improves the smallest-K point. Increasing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at K=32 may further strengthen the low-cost end of the Pareto frontier if the K=32 residual branch is currently capacity-limited.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` stabilization pass at `K=32` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, keeping the rest of the winning recipe fixed (`OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This checks whether the capacity gain that helped at K=64 also improves the K=32 frontier point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps variable isolation clean and extends the only confirmed positive family-specific tuning signal to the most cost-sensitive frontier point. The main risk is that EF=32 helps at K=64 but not at K=32, adding cost without enough quality gain, but that boundary is important to establish before trying aux or K=128 capacity tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 20 extends the successful `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` stabilization signal within `lowrank_residual` from K=64 down to K=32.","The next missing question for this family-specific capacity axis is whether the smallest-K frontier point is also residual-capacity limited or whether EF=16 is already sufficient there."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improves proxy FVU at K=32, promote it to full and then consider the same capacity increase at K=128.","If EF=32 is flat or worse at K=32, keep EF=16 for that point and test a different single stabilization axis such as `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` on one of the winning anchors.","If EF=32 improves K=32 quality but causes clear runtime or memory regression, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code pass rather than discarding the higher-capacity variant outright."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0030.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent lowrank_gated_residual sweeps exhausted local LR/aux/EF tuning without improving the K=128 anchor, and policy blocks opening a third incubating family. The least-bad informative move is to advance the existing incubating `whitened_topk` family by strengthening its preconditioner: normalize activations first, then apply a low-rank residual mixer around identity before TopK selection. If the earlier `whitened_topk` result failed because its shallow raw linear map was too weak and poorly conditioned, this stabilized geometry change could reopen quality gains under the current strong recipe.","summary":"Edit `whitened_topk` in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` so it uses RMS-normalized inputs plus a low-rank residual preconditioner instead of a single dense raw linear map, then run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This keeps the round focused on one architectural variable while advancing an existing incubating family rather than opening a policy-risky new one.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"whitened_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This respects the severe-stagnation guidance by pivoting away from more lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning, but avoids the likely incubation-limit rejection of a brand-new family. The code change is confined to `sparsify/`, keeps the execution layer untouched, and a local forward/backward smoke test passed for the edited `whitened_topk` path.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Advanced the existing incubating `whitened_topk` family instead of opening a new family, to avoid incubation-limit risk during severe stagnation.","Reworked `WhitenedTopKSparseCoder` to encode from RMS-normalized activations passed through a low-rank residual preconditioner initialized near identity, replacing the earlier shallow dense raw preconditioner.","Local CPU forward/backward smoke test passed for the edited `whitened_topk` implementation."],"next_hypotheses":["If the stabilized `whitened_topk` proxy becomes competitive, promote to full before any further family-local tuning.","If proxy quality improves but throughput regresses, follow with a narrow `edit_perf_code` pass on the new preconditioner path rather than discarding the family.","If the stronger preconditioner still leaves `whitened_topk` far behind, archive input-preconditioning-only approaches and pivot back to a different architecture mechanism rather than more local retuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0098.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The exact active point `(K=40, EF=12)` has now rejected several fundamentally different mechanisms, and the one non-TopK family with the best remaining same-EF low-K signal is `two_code_residual_vq`. Since lower K is the top priority and `K=32, EF=12` is still sparsely explored outside the residual baseline, the next informative move is to map this discrete coarse-plus-residual family down to `K=32` before spending another round on EF or another new local tweak.","summary":"Run a proxy `two_code_residual_vq` experiment at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This keeps the comparison in the low-K tradeoff lane, uses the default same-EF band, tests a fundamentally different architecture family from the residual/gating path, and prioritizes lower-K exploration over more EF work.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"two_code_residual_vq","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a single-variable low-K probe on an already repaired and runnable discrete family, so the result should be interpretable. The risk is that `two_code_residual_vq` simply degrades too much at `K=32`, but that is still more useful than another minor recipe tweak or another same-K mechanism swap after 46 no-improve rounds.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_code_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 98 maps `two_code_residual_vq` from `K=40` to `K=32` at the same `EF=12` mainline band to honor the low-K priority while keeping a fundamentally different architecture family alive.","This is a same-EF low-K tradeoff test, not a claim of architecture improvement from added capacity.","If `two_code_residual_vq` is also weak at `K=32`, that is additional evidence that the current low-K reconstruction-only discrete-family path is not closing the frontier gap and the next move should be a stronger reformulation rather than another small mechanism swap."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_code_residual_vq` is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and judge it as a real low-K tradeoff candidate before any EF follow-up.","If `two_code_residual_vq` is clearly weak at `K=32, EF=12`, pivot next to a genuinely new problem reformulation or architecture family rather than more local low-K retuning within the current mechanism set."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` also regressed badly in proxy, so the current question is no longer whether the leading family survives small capacity but whether any other architecture does better at the same lower-K, same-EF target. The next cleanest move is to hold `K=40`, `EF=8`, optimizer, LR, and aux fixed and switch only the architecture to `two_stage_residual`, which has prior nontrivial full-signal evidence and is the strongest remaining fair challenger in this small-EF comparison band.","summary":"Run a proxy architecture comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=40`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=8`, keeping `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This preserves single-variable isolation, respects the `EF<=16` cap and `EF=8` default, continues the lower-K priority at `K=40`, and tests whether hierarchical residual allocation is a better small-capacity architecture than both `lowrank_residual` and `lowrank_gated_residual` at the same budget.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"medium","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is the cleanest next comparison after both small-EF low-rank families underperformed at `K=40`. It keeps the search on the prioritized lower-K track, avoids banned `EF=32` continuation, and changes only architecture.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"two_stage_residual","K":"40","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"8","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0.0"},"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 49 showed `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also weak in proxy (`val_fvu=0.17895471677184105`), so the small-EF rebuild of the frontier should not stay family-local.","Both `lowrank_residual` and `lowrank_gated_residual` now look uncompetitive at `K=40`, `EF=8`, which strengthens the case for a same-K, same-EF comparison against `two_stage_residual` rather than any EF increase.","Keep `K=40` as the current lower-K anchor while rebuilding fair `EF=8` architecture comparisons; do not resume `EF=32` runs."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full as the first fair small-EF lower-K challenger with nontrivial signal.","If `two_stage_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also weak, end this small-EF comparison cluster and pivot to a different mechanism family at the same `K=40`, `EF=8` target rather than increasing EF.","If `two_stage_residual` shows better quality but poor runtime behavior, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code fix instead of discarding the family on proxy quality alone."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0033.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Eight no-improve rounds indicate the current lowrank_gated_residual tuning track is exhausted, and the frontier already covers K={32,64,128}, so the next informative move must switch the single primary variable back to architecture. The cleanest fundamentally different probe is to re-benchmark `jumprelu` at K=128 under the current strongest shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`) to test whether a different sparse activation mechanism benefits from the stronger mainline training regime that earlier non-gated families did not fully share.","summary":"Run a proxy comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=jumprelu` at K=128 using the current strong shared lowrank_gated_residual training recipe, changing only architecture. This satisfies the mandatory architecture pivot after repeated stagnation while avoiding new code risk and giving the only remaining incubating family a fair comparison under today's strongest stable setup.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This round stops the failed minor-parameter loop on `lowrank_gated_residual` and isolates a genuine architecture change with no code edits. It also uses an existing working architecture path, which is lower risk than opening another new family after recent crash and identical-to-baseline failures.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation forced a pivot away from further lowrank_gated_residual parameter sweeps and back to a fundamentally different architecture.","`jumprelu` is the selected comparison target because it is the only remaining incubating family with a stable existing code path and no new implementation risk this round.","This run tests whether the current strongest shared recipe changes the verdict on `jumprelu` relative to its much weaker earlier evidence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` is competitive at K=128 proxy, promote it to full before any further family-local tuning.","If `jumprelu` remains clearly behind, archive it and plan the next round around a different architecture mechanism rather than more lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning.","If `jumprelu` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code fix instead of discarding the architecture on quality grounds."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0066.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"In crash-recovery mode, the safest informative move is to stay on the known working `lowrank_gated_residual` small-EF recipe and step K down from the last stable `K=64` probe to `K=56`, testing whether a lower-K point can still run cleanly while improving the low-K map.","summary":"Use the current best working family and shared stable optimizer/LR recipe, keep `EF=8` fixed, and change only `K` from the last stable small-EF recovery point to `56`. This preserves stability-first behavior while continuing the required lower-K exploration without touching code.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash-recovery constraints exactly: no code edits, same known-good family, one minor parameter change, and a lower-K move from the last clean run. The risk is another weak proxy result, but it should restore a stable signal before any further architecture work.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"56"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 66 is constrained by crash-recovery mode, so it reverts to the known working `lowrank_gated_residual` family with no code changes.","This recovery probe keeps the stable small-EF recipe fixed and changes only `K` from the prior stable `K=64` point down to `K=56` to continue lower-K mapping conservatively.","If this run is stable, use it as the new recovery anchor before resuming broader architecture exploration; if it crashes, treat the issue as broader runtime instability rather than an architecture conclusion."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=56`, `EF=8` runs cleanly, continue the recovery sweep to a nearby lower K such as `K=48` before changing architecture again.","If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=56`, `EF=8` crashes despite being a known working family, stay in stability-first mode and try an even more conservative parameter-only recovery move rather than any code or architecture change."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0062.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A separate support router may preserve more useful structure than pure magnitude TopK at very low sparsity, so a `routed` SAE at `K=32`, `EF=8` is the next clean architecture pivot to test whether low-K quality improves through different support selection rather than more residual-branch variants.","summary":"Pivot away from the weak grouped-residual path and run a fresh same-EF architecture probe with `routed` at the lower-K target `K=32`. This keeps capacity fixed in the preferred small-EF band while testing a fundamentally different low-K mechanism that perturbs support selection directly instead of relying on grouped residual competition.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture and keeps the focus on lower K without using a larger EF. Main risk is that `routed` may behave similarly to existing gated variants, but it is still a distinct support-selection mechanism and a cleaner next probe than more local tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 62 pivots away from `lowrank_grouped_residual` after its `K=40`, `EF=8` proxy remained weak, and tests a fundamentally different low-K routing mechanism instead of another residual-family follow-up.","`routed` is being probed at `K=32`, `EF=8` to keep lower-K exploration primary while preserving same-EF comparability.","If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak, treat direct support-selection variants as another negative signal in the small-EF low-K band and continue pivoting rather than resuming minor sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, keep the family fixed and map a nearby K such as `K=40` before touching EF.","If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is weak, try another fundamentally different low-K family at the same `EF=8` target, such as a preprocessing-oriented or mixture-style direction, rather than increasing expansion factor."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0049.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` was clearly weak in proxy, so the next fair small-capacity comparison should keep the same `K=40`, `EF=8`, optimizer, and LR while switching only architecture. Testing `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is the strongest same-EF follow-up because it is the current best overall family and will show whether the low-K frontier remains viable once the operator-mandated capacity cap is enforced.","summary":"Run a proxy architecture comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_gated_residual`, `K=40`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=8`, keeping `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This preserves variable isolation, respects the `EF<=16` cap, and gives the leading family a fair small-EF benchmark at the current lower-K target.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This follows the updated small-EF search regime and fixes the prior round's variable-isolation issue by keeping `K` and `EF` fixed while changing only architecture. Main risk: the family may also degrade sharply at `EF=8`, but that negative result would still be a clean and informative same-EF comparison.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 48 showed `lowrank_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is not competitive enough in proxy, so the next fair step is another same-`K`, same-`EF` architecture comparison rather than changing capacity.","The operator guidance now requires ending the old `EF=32` track and rebuilding comparisons at `EF=8`, so `lowrank_gated_residual` needs a clean `K=40`, `EF=8` benchmark before broader conclusions about low-K viability at small EF are made."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full as the first strong small-EF checkpoint for the current leading family.","If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also weak, keep `K=40`, `EF=8` fixed and compare another architecture such as `two_stage_residual` rather than increasing EF."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0081.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`residual_vq_topk` still has not produced a real low-K signal because the prototype failed at the implementation layer before training, so the next move is one more narrow code-fix pass to make the existing `K=32`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` experiment runnable without changing its design.","summary":"Do a repair-focused pass on the existing `residual_vq_topk` prototype under `sparsify/` so the original proxy target can actually launch and survive sanity/startup. Keep the family, tier, and override set fixed; only patch the concrete implementation blocker.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This stays within the crash-repair-first rule and does not spend another round on parameter churn. The prototype has not earned a quality verdict yet because it has not run successfully, so one more narrow repair attempt is more informative than abandoning or redesigning it immediately.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["`residual_vq_topk` remains an implementation-blocked prototype rather than a judged architecture result until it completes a real run.","Keep repair scope narrow and confined to startup/sanity compatibility for the existing experiment target; do not redesign the family during repair.","If the next repair succeeds and the run completes, judge the family on quality; if it fails again with a new concrete blocker, continue only with another narrowly scoped repair."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq_topk` launches and completes, evaluate whether the discrete coarse-plus-residual framing is competitive enough to keep incubating at low K.","If a new concrete forward/backward or DDP compatibility error appears, do one more narrow repair pass with the same experiment target rather than changing architecture or overrides.","If the repaired prototype runs cleanly but is clearly weak, archive `residual_vq_topk` on quality grounds and pivot to a different fundamentally different family."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0005.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` produced the strongest non-gated proxy among recent architecture pivots, so the next informative move is a narrow family-specific stabilization pass rather than abandoning it after one prototype result. The current trunk rank formula likely underpowers the dense trunk under the strong EF=16 recipe by collapsing to a near-minimal rank, so increasing the default trunk capacity should remove more shared dense structure before sparse residual coding and improve FVU at fixed K=128.","summary":"Strengthen the internal low-rank trunk in `lowrank_residual` and rerun the same K=128 proxy comparison under the shared best signum recipe. This keeps the round focused on one architecture-family code change with no launcher or metric changes.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"I kept the round to one primary change inside the incubating `lowrank_residual` family, avoided another minor gated tweak, and verified the edited model still passes a local forward/backward smoke test.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Adjusted `lowrank_residual` trunk sizing to `min(d_in, max(2*k, d_in//4))` so the dense trunk is not implicitly weakened by the shared EF=16 recipe.","Local smoke test after the edit succeeded for `lowrank_residual` forward/backward, with trunk rank 256 at `d_in=1024, k=128`.","This round isolates a family-specific stabilization hypothesis for `lowrank_residual` after its initial proxy beat `jumprelu` but remained well behind gated."],"next_hypotheses":["If the stronger-trunk `lowrank_residual` materially improves proxy FVU, keep incubating the family and then explore lower K within this family or promote to full if the gain is large enough.","If quality stays similar but throughput regresses, follow with a targeted `edit_perf_code` round rather than treating the family as architecturally weak.","If the stronger trunk still leaves `lowrank_residual` clearly uncompetitive, pivot to a different fundamentally new architecture family instead of returning to gated-local tuning."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0037.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Twelve no-improve rounds indicate that the current search direction is fundamentally flawed, and the latest alternative sparse-allocation families still sit far behind the frontier. The next coherent architecture move is to test conditionalized dictionaries rather than another global-allocation variant: add `bucketed_topk`, which routes samples between separate low-norm and high-norm dictionaries before TopK selection. If the activation distribution is multi-regime rather than unimodal, specializing dictionaries by sample norm could improve reconstruction quality without changing the fixed execution layer.","summary":"Add a new `bucketed_topk` family under `sparsify/` and run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This is a fundamentally different architecture probe that tests conditional mixture-of-dictionaries behavior instead of more tuning on fixed or batch-global support allocation.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This round changes one core variable only, the architecture, and keeps all launcher and metric semantics fixed. The implementation is confined to `sparsify/`, registers through the existing validation/factory path, and a local forward/backward smoke test passed for the new conditional dictionary route.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added `bucketed_topk`, a conditional dictionary architecture that mixes separate low-norm and high-norm encoder branches before TopK selection.","Registered `bucketed_topk` in the existing architecture validation and factory paths under `sparsify/` only.","Local smoke test passed for `bucketed_topk` forward/backward execution, confirming the new route is trainable under the current codebase."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_topk` is competitive at K=128 proxy, keep the family alive and promote it to full before any local tuning.","If `bucketed_topk` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented `code_fix` on the conditional routing path rather than discarding the family immediately.","If `bucketed_topk` remains clearly behind, archive norm-bucketed conditional dictionaries and pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism rather than returning to lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0093.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Single-code `residual_vq` was clearly too coarse at low K, and both routed and residual-magnitude alternatives have now failed to improve the `K=40, EF=12` local frontier. A real `two_code_residual_vq` prototype that composes two hard codebook selections before the sparse residual stage is the next informative architecture move because it strengthens the discrete trunk without raising K or EF.","summary":"Implement `two_code_residual_vq` under `sparsify/` and run its first proxy comparison at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This uses a fundamentally different architecture at the exact active comparison point and avoids more same-family local tuning after extended stagnation.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_code_residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a genuine architecture change at the same `(K, EF)` target and directly addresses the current failure mode of weak low-K discrete capacity. The main risk is another weak first prototype, but it is more informative than further K mapping on families that have already stalled.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_code_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 93 revisits the blocked `two_code_residual_vq` direction as the next fundamentally different low-K architecture move after routed and lowrank_residual both failed to beat the `K=40, EF=12` local baseline.","The target stays fixed at `K=40, EF=12` so the signal is directly comparable within the active low-K lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_code_residual_vq` at `K=40, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and test `K=32, EF=12` to see whether the stronger discrete trunk improves the lower-K Pareto tradeoff.","If it runs cleanly but is weak, archive the discrete residual-VQ branch and free incubation capacity for a different low-K family rather than continuing more residual-VQ variants."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five rounds of gated-local tuning have failed to move the frontier, so the current search direction is likely locally exhausted. The least-disruptive fundamentally different probe is to switch the single primary variable back to architecture and run `jumprelu` at K=128 under the strongest shared signum recipe to test whether a different sparse activation mechanism can reopen quality gains without introducing new code risk.","summary":"Run a `jumprelu` proxy comparison at K=128 under the stable signum/EF=16/aux-free regime, changing only architecture from gated to jumprelu.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This satisfies the severe-stagnation requirement by abandoning minor gated parameter tweaks and switching to a fundamentally different existing architecture family with prior full-signal evidence. It keeps the round isolated to one variable, avoids blocked code-fix paths, and uses proxy first.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation triggered an architecture pivot away from further gated-local tuning.","This round revisits the best existing non-gated family under the current strongest shared recipe to test whether the search failure is specific to gated rather than the whole regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` materially improves proxy FVU, promote it to full and treat it as the main alternative trunk for further stabilization.","If `jumprelu` remains clearly behind gated under the shared strong recipe, the next move should be a different architecture path or a narrow compatibility repair for an incubating family rather than more gated parameter sweeps."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0090.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With incubation slots saturated and recent fresh-family probes weak or blocked, the least-bad informative move is to return to the strongest existing alternative architecture at the active low-K target. `lowrank_residual` is the closest non-gated same-`(K=32, EF=12)` competitor seen so far, so rerunning that exact architecture point is the best available architecture-level comparison against the weak discrete branch and the slightly better gated local baseline.","summary":"Run a proxy mainline comparison for `lowrank_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This avoids another minor parameter tweak, stays in the exact low-K neighborhood, and uses an already-implemented fundamentally different family while the incubation limit blocks opening more new families.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round architecture-focused without spending another incubation slot, and it compares families fairly at the same `K` and `EF`. The downside is that this exact point has prior evidence and may simply confirm weakness, but under the current slot pressure it is the most defensible architecture move available.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 90 uses the strongest already-implemented non-gated alternative, `lowrank_residual`, for a same-`(K=32, EF=12)` architecture comparison because incubation slots are saturated.","This round is intended to refresh the exact low-K local comparison against `lowrank_gated_residual` and `residual_vq` without introducing another new family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` is now competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40, EF=12` before touching EF.","If it remains weak, archive stale incubating families that are clearly uncompetitive and use the freed slot for a genuinely new low-K architecture family rather than more local retuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0031.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 30 showed that the revised `whitened_topk` path still trips the runtime's behavioral-diff gate as identical to baseline, so this round should repair that blocker instead of opening another architecture or returning to exhausted lowrank-gated sweeps. By making `whitened_topk` explicitly mean-center each sample and inject a fixed cross-channel roll mix before the learned low-rank preconditioner, the family should become observably distinct from plain top-k at step 0 while preserving the same input-geometry hypothesis.","summary":"Apply a narrow `code_fix` to `whitened_topk` in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` so its encode path uses per-sample centering, RMS normalization, and a fixed rolled-channel mix before the low-rank residual preconditioner, then rerun the same K=128 proxy comparison under the strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This keeps the round focused on unblocking an existing incubating family rather than spending another round on minor parameter tweaks.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"whitened_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This round addresses the highest-priority blocker from the last result instead of misreading an `identical_to_baseline` abort as an architecture-quality failure. The change is confined to `sparsify/`, keeps one primary variable isolated as a code-path repair inside the same family, and a local smoke check confirmed nonzero activation and support differences versus baseline top-k while preserving forward/backward execution.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repaired the `whitened_topk` encode path after round 30's `identical_to_baseline` abort by adding per-sample centering and a fixed rolled-channel mix before sparse selection.","Local differential smoke check against plain `topk` now shows clear step-0 divergence for `whitened_topk` with shared encoder weights, including nonzero top-activation differences and changed support indices.","This round should be interpreted as a blocker-removal pass for the incubating input-preconditioning family, not as another new-family launch or a lowrank_gated_residual retune."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `whitened_topk` proxy is competitive, keep the family alive and consider a full run before further family-local tuning.","If `whitened_topk` now runs but remains far behind, archive input-preconditioning-only approaches and pivot to a different fundamentally different sparse mechanism rather than more local retuning.","If quality is promising but runtime is flagged as slow, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass on the preconditioning path rather than discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0080_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Patch the existing `residual_vq_topk` prototype registration so the original low-K proxy experiment can instantiate and run under the unchanged `K=32`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` target.","summary":"Repair the concrete launcher blocker by adding `residual_vq_topk` to architecture validation and SAE factory dispatch under `sparsify/`, without changing the experiment target or override set.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair stays narrowly scoped to the observed blocker: the new architecture name was not registered, so training failed before startup. The experiment design, family, and overrides remain unchanged.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 addresses a concrete registration blocker: `residual_vq_topk` was missing from config validation and SAE class dispatch.","Keep the experiment target fixed during repair; do not change family, tier, or env overrides until the prototype can launch.","If this registration repair succeeds but a new runtime error appears, handle that as the next narrow implementation blocker rather than redesigning the experiment."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registration repair works and the run completes, evaluate `residual_vq_topk` on its original low-K proxy merits before any follow-up.","If a new concrete implementation or DDP compatibility error appears after registration, do one additional narrow repair pass with the same experiment target.","If the repaired prototype runs and is clearly weak, archive the family on quality grounds rather than continuing repair-only work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0011.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` remains a real K=128 win, but the front-loaded split change only matched the existing best point instead of extending the frontier, and its lower-K/width behavior still looks brittle. The next informative move is to pivot to a different non-gated family with a different inductive bias: a `multi_branch_gated` SAE that uses several gated encoder branches competing to explain different activation substructures before the final TopK selection, which could preserve the K=128 quality gains while avoiding the narrow tuning sensitivity of the staged-residual prototype.","summary":"Add a `multi_branch_gated` prototype under `sparsify/` and run a proxy comparison at K=128 using the current signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe, changing only architecture.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"multi_branch_gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the observed plateau correctly: the `two_stage_residual` family is no longer extending the frontier through local internal tweaks, so a new architecture family is the least-bad next move. Risk: a first prototype may trail the current winner, but it is a cleaner use of the next round than more blind stabilization on a family that just went flat.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"multi_branch_gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The front-loaded `two_stage_residual` stabilization pass reproduced the existing K=128 best result but did not improve it, so additional blind family-local tweaks are no longer the best use of the next round.","This round pivots to a new `multi_branch_gated` family to test a different encoder bias at the same K=128 anchor under the strongest current training recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `multi_branch_gated` produces a competitive proxy result, keep incubating it with family-specific branch-width or branch-allocation stabilization.","If it is clearly uncompetitive, deprioritize more multi-branch routing variants and consider a more radically different sparse mechanism next.","If quality is promising but runtime is poor, follow with a targeted performance pass rather than discarding the family immediately."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0016.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five no-improve rounds suggest the current `two_stage_residual` direction is locally exhausted, so this round should switch the single primary variable back to architecture. The strongest informative alternative is `lowrank_residual`, which attacks the plateau by modeling shared dense structure with a low-rank trunk before sparse residual coding, and should be re-tested at K=128 under the current strongest shared recipe for a clean apples-to-apples comparison.","summary":"Run a proxy comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_residual` at K=128 using the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=16`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This is a fundamentally different architecture probe after the `two_stage_residual` LR sweep failed to improve the frontier.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the mandatory pivot away from minor parameter tweaks, keeps one primary variable isolated at the architecture level, and chooses the most plausible incubating alternative rather than opening a brand-new family. The main risk is that `lowrank_residual` remains clearly behind the frontier or exposes residual implementation fragility, but that is still more informative than another local sweep on the stalled mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 16 obeys the severe-stagnation pivot by abandoning further `two_stage_residual` micro-sweeps and changing only architecture.","`lowrank_residual` is the selected comparison target because it is the strongest recent fundamentally different incubating family and directly tests whether separating dense trunk structure from sparse residual coding can break the K=128 plateau."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` materially improves proxy FVU, keep incubating it and consider a family-specific stabilization pass or promotion depending on margin.","If `lowrank_residual` runs but stays clearly behind, pivot to another fundamentally different incubating family such as `whitened_topk` rather than returning to `two_stage_residual` micro-tuning.","If `lowrank_residual` shows promising quality with poor throughput or instability, follow with a narrow code-focused stabilization or performance pass instead of discarding the family outright."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0100.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The low-K lane has repeatedly rejected support-selection tweaks, whitening variants, and discrete residual families, so the strongest pending informative move is to execute the newly added `bucketed_lowrank_residual` reformulation at the exact active target. Conditioning the residual dictionary on coarse sample regime may recover useful low-K capacity where single-dictionary residual models and other mechanism swaps have stalled, without changing K or EF.","summary":"Run the first proxy measurement for `bucketed_lowrank_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This keeps the experiment in the active low-K lane, preserves same-EF comparability, and tests the new conditional-dictionary reformulation before opening another family or touching EF.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the cleanest next step because the family was just added and directly targets the current suspected failure mode of heterogeneous residual structure at low K. The main risk is that norm-based bucketing is too crude to help, but running it now is still more informative than another minor local tweak or another cross-family detour.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 100 executes the first proxy run for `bucketed_lowrank_residual` at the active low-K target `K=32, EF=12` after the round-99 architecture addition.","This remains a same-EF low-K comparison and tests conditional residual specialization rather than another support-selection or VQ-style mechanism swap.","If the family is weak here, that further supports moving the next architecture step toward a deeper objective or problem reformulation instead of continuing to add more incubating low-K families."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and map it to `K=40, EF=12` before any EF work.","If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is clearly weak under normal runtime, archive stale weak incubating families and pivot the next move toward a stronger objective-level reformulation rather than another architecture-local tweak."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0042.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash-recovery policy forces a param-only round on the best proven working family. Rather than retrying already-regressed LR/aux/EF sweeps at the K=128 anchor, the cleanest stable move is to hold the winning `lowrank_gated_residual` recipe fixed and lower only `K` to 96 in proxy. This maps a missing mid-Pareto point between 64 and 128 and could yield a non-dominated tradeoff if quality stays close to the K=128 anchor while reducing active feature count.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_gated_residual` experiment at `K=96` using the current best working recipe otherwise unchanged: `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`, `BATCH_SIZE=1`, `GRAD_ACC_STEPS=8`, `MICRO_ACC_STEPS=1`, `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD=10000000`, `USE_HADAMARD=0`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This obeys the param-only crash-recovery constraint, stays on the strongest validated family, and changes one substantive experimental variable: `K`. It does not chase a weakly motivated LR/aux retry, and it targets Pareto expansion directly. Main risk: the project runtime may still judge this too close to existing K sweeps, but it is the safest informative probe available without code changes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash-recovery policy required a param-only round on the best working configuration; this round uses `lowrank_gated_residual` with only `K` changed substantively.","`K=96` is an explicit mid-frontier probe between the established `K=64` and `K=128` points, aimed at expanding Pareto coverage rather than only improving the anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=96` proxy is close to the `K=128` proxy anchor, promote it to full as a likely non-dominated Pareto point.","If `K=96` falls much closer to the `K=64` quality level than the `K=128` level, keep `K` focus but try a nearby midpoint like `K=80` only if policy still prefers stable param-only frontier mapping."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0007_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent alternative families remain well behind gated at K=128, so the next informative move is a genuinely different encoder structure rather than another local sweep. A new `two_stage_residual` SAE that allocates the same total K across a coarse sparse pass and a residual sparse pass may recover more variance at fixed sparsity by turning single-shot TopK selection into staged residual reconstruction.","summary":"Patch the existing `two_stage_residual` prototype under `sparsify/` so the planned proxy comparison at K=128 can instantiate and run under the current best signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"unblock_run","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair stays narrowly focused on the concrete blocker: `two_stage_residual` was missing from architecture validation and factory dispatch, so training crashed before startup. The patch adds the architecture registration plus a minimal runnable implementation, and a local forward/backward instantiate check passed.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 for round 7 fixed the concrete startup blocker by registering `two_stage_residual` in config validation and SAE factory dispatch.","Added a minimal `TwoStageResidualSparseCoder` implementation in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`; local instantiate plus forward/backward sanity passed."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `two_stage_residual` run now completes and shows promising proxy FVU, continue the original incubation plan for this family.","If the next failure is another concrete implementation bug, continue repair mode without changing the experiment target.","If the run completes but is slow, consider a later performance-focused follow-up rather than abandoning the family immediately."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0048.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `lowrank_gated_residual` K sweep at `EF=32` has now mapped a clear lower-K frontier down to `K=40`, and the new operator hint explicitly rules out further `EF=32` runs. The next most informative move is a same-EF architecture comparison at lower K: run `lowrank_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` under the shared stable optimizer/LR recipe to test whether a simpler low-rank residual family preserves more quality at small K when capacity is reduced to the newly preferred regime.","summary":"Run a proxy architecture comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_residual`, `K=40`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=8`, keeping `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This ends the disallowed `EF=32` sweep, respects the new `EF<=16` cap, and tests a promising alternative family at a lower-K target.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This pivots away from the saturated `lowrank_gated_residual` `EF=32` track and follows the new EF cap. The main risk is that moving to both a new architecture family and a smaller EF may underperform the old large-capacity frontier, but this is still a single primary-variable architecture comparison under the updated capacity regime rather than another forbidden `EF=32` sweep.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 47 full showed the `lowrank_gated_residual` `EF=32` K sweep has reached a useful boundary at `K=40`, and a new operator hint now forbids further `EF=32` experiments.","The next search phase should use `EF<=16` and prefer `EF=8`, so refreshed architecture comparisons should restart in that smaller-capacity regime rather than claiming wins from the old `EF=32` frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full as the first fair small-EF architecture comparison at lower K.","If `lowrank_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is clearly weak, keep the same `K=40`, `EF=8` target and try another architecture family such as `lowrank_gated_residual` or `two_stage_residual` rather than increasing EF."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0071.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent fixed-point `K=48`, `EF=16` mechanism probes were both clearly weak, so the next informative move is to change the search framing and test a routing-based sparse mechanism at a smaller K in the preferred mainline band. Run `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to check whether explicit support routing recovers a viable low-K tradeoff better than magnitude-style TopK variants.","summary":"Pivot from the failed `K=48` TopK-mechanism cluster to a routing-based architecture at lower K. This uses `EF=12` as the default refreshed comparison band and keeps optimizer settings fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round architecture-led under severe stagnation and shifts to a genuinely different mechanism instead of another local tweak. The main risk is that `routed` was already weak at `EF=8`, but rerunning it in the preferred `EF=12` band at the same low-K target is a cleaner read than continuing archived TopK-style families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 71 abandons the weak `K=48` TopK-style comparison cluster and pivots to a routing-based mechanism at lower K.","`routed` is refreshed in the preferred mainline band with `EF=12` rather than returning to `EF=8`, which should separate architecture quality from the earlier capacity floor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is still weak, pivot to another fundamentally different non-TopK direction in the same mainline band rather than reopening archived TopK-family comparisons."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0099.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The low-K lane has now rejected several support-selection tweaks and discrete residual variants, which suggests the failure mode may be a single global dictionary trying to cover heterogeneous samples rather than the exact sparse mechanism alone. A new `bucketed_lowrank_residual` family that keeps the proven low-rank trunk but routes samples between two residual dictionaries by activation norm can test a stronger problem reformulation at the active target `K=32, EF=12` without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Add a new `bucketed_lowrank_residual` architecture under `sparsify/` and run its first proxy comparison at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This is a fundamentally different architecture approach in the active low-K lane: conditional residual specialization instead of another local sparsity-rule tweak or another cross-EF move.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single coherent architecture bet aimed at the current failure mode: heterogeneity within the residual space at low K. The risk is that simple norm-based bucketing may be too crude to help, but it is materially more different than another threshold/gating/VQ variant and stays directly comparable at the exact active `(K, EF)` point.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 99 pivots from repeated low-K mechanism failures to a stronger reformulation: conditional residual dictionaries via a new `bucketed_lowrank_residual` family.","The new family keeps the low-rank trunk prior but replaces the single residual dictionary with norm-conditioned specialization so low-K capacity can be allocated by sample regime without raising K.","This remains a same-EF comparison in the active low-K lane and does not rely on larger expansion factor as a rescue path."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and map it to `K=40, EF=12` before any EF work.","If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is clearly weak under normal runtime, treat that as further evidence that the next move should target a deeper objective reformulation rather than more architecture-local support-allocation tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0024.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` has now improved the full frontier at both K=128 and K=64, so the next clean move is to change only K again and test whether the family also strengthens the smallest currently active Pareto point. A proxy K=32 run under the same EF=32 signum recipe will show whether the gated residual selector is a general frontier improvement rather than only a medium/high-K gain.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=32 while holding EF=32, signum, LR=1.6e-3, and AUXK_ALPHA=0 fixed. This directly tests whether the new family can replace `lowrank_residual` across the full current Pareto set by improving the smallest-K point as well.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one primary variable, `k`, and follows the family-specific stabilization sequence opened by the successful K=128 and K=64 full results. It is the highest-value next check because it can either complete a coherent frontier takeover for the family or cleanly bound where its gains stop.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 24 tests `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=32 after full wins at K=128 and K=64 under the shared EF=32 signum recipe.","This is the next stabilization step needed to determine whether `lowrank_gated_residual` can become the mainline family across the whole current Pareto frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` improves proxy FVU at K=32, promote it to full and treat the family as the leading mainline across K={32,64,128}.","If K=32 is flat or worse, keep `lowrank_gated_residual` as the better family for K>=64 and consider a single-variable internal stabilization move such as `AUXK_ALPHA` within this family.","If K=32 quality is promising but runtime is flagged as a perf regression, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass instead of concluding against the architecture."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0036.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Eleven no-improve rounds indicate the fixed-per-sample sparse allocation direction is fundamentally flawed, and recent alternatives like `jumprelu`, `two_stage_residual`, and `adaptive_budget_topk` still stayed far behind the frontier. The next coherent architecture move is to test a cleaner batch-level sparsity mechanism: add `batch_topk`, which enforces the same total activation budget across the batch but selects features globally rather than distributing them per sample or via a heuristic quota. If the main failure mode is rigid per-sample support allocation, true batch-level competition could improve reconstruction quality at fixed average sparsity.","summary":"Add a new `batch_topk` family under `sparsify/` and run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This is a fundamentally different architecture probe that directly tests batch-level global support allocation instead of continuing any low-signal tuning on the current mainline.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"batch_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This round changes one core variable only, the sparse allocation mechanism, and keeps the execution layer untouched. The implementation is confined to `sparsify/`, registers through the existing config/factory path, and a local forward/backward smoke test passed with visibly non-uniform per-sample active counts under a shared batch budget.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"batch_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added `batch_topk`, a new sparse architecture that selects features under a global batch-level budget instead of enforcing fixed per-sample K.","Registered `batch_topk` in the existing architecture validation and factory paths under `sparsify/` only.","Local smoke test passed for `batch_topk` forward/backward execution, and the encoded supports showed non-uniform per-sample active counts under batch execution."],"next_hypotheses":["If `batch_topk` is competitive at K=128 proxy, keep the family alive and promote to full before local tuning.","If `batch_topk` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented `code_fix` on the batch-global selection path rather than discarding the family immediately.","If `batch_topk` remains clearly behind, archive batch-level global allocation and pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism rather than returning to lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0022.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current `lowrank_residual` family has finished a clean EF=32 stabilization sweep across K={32,64,128}, and the search has gone many rounds without a new family. A narrow next bet is to keep the winning low-rank trunk intact and change only the sparse residual selector: add a gated residual branch so support selection can focus sparse capacity on the hardest residual directions at the K=128 quality anchor. If low-rank decomposition is already the right backbone, this should be a higher-signal architecture probe than another local sweep on the existing family.","summary":"Implemented a new `lowrank_gated_residual` architecture under `sparsify/` and validated it with a local import + forward/backward sanity check. Run a proxy K=128 comparison against the current winning low-rank recipe, holding EF=32, signum, LR=1.6e-3, and AUXK_ALPHA=0 fixed while switching only the architecture.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps the round to one coherent primary variable: architecture. The new family is intentionally minimal, reusing the proven low-rank trunk and existing gated mechanics to reduce implementation risk while still testing a genuinely new support-selection hypothesis at the main quality anchor.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added `lowrank_gated_residual`, which keeps the successful low-rank dense trunk but gates sparse residual support selection with a learned residual router.","Local CPU import plus forward/backward sanity check passed for `lowrank_gated_residual`; the new family is ready for runtime sanity and proxy evaluation."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` shows better proxy FVU at K=128, promote it to full before exploring lower-K variants.","If proxy quality is close but runtime is flagged as a perf regression, follow with an `edit_perf_code` pass rather than discarding the family.","If the gated residual selector is clearly worse at K=128, keep `lowrank_residual` as mainline and explore a different new family rather than more local retuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0011_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` remains a real K=128 win, but the front-loaded split change only matched the existing best point instead of extending the frontier, and its lower-K/width behavior still looks brittle. The next informative move is to pivot to a different non-gated family with a different inductive bias: a `multi_branch_gated` SAE that uses several gated encoder branches competing to explain different activation substructures before the final TopK selection, which could preserve the K=128 quality gains while avoiding the narrow tuning sensitivity of the staged-residual prototype.","summary":"Patch the existing `multi_branch_gated` prototype under `sparsify/` so the planned proxy comparison at K=128 can instantiate and run under the current signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"unblock_run","family_name":"multi_branch_gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair stays narrowly focused on the concrete blocker: `multi_branch_gated` was missing from architecture validation and SAE factory dispatch, so training crashed before startup. The patch adds registration plus a minimal runnable implementation, and a local instantiate plus forward/backward check passed.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"multi_branch_gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 for round 11 fixed the concrete startup blocker by registering `multi_branch_gated` in config validation and SAE factory dispatch.","Added a minimal `MultiBranchGatedSparseCoder` implementation in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`; local instantiate plus forward/backward sanity passed."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `multi_branch_gated` run now completes and shows competitive proxy FVU, continue the original incubation plan for this family.","If the next failure is another concrete implementation bug, continue repair mode without changing the experiment target.","If the run completes but is slow, consider a later performance-focused follow-up rather than abandoning the family immediately."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0101.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`bucketed_lowrank_residual` did not fail on quality; it failed on a narrow implementation blocker because the architecture string was not registered in config validation and/or factory dispatch. The correct next move is a repair-only follow-up that wires the existing family into the `sparsify/` registration path and reruns the exact same `K=32, EF=12` proxy target unchanged.","summary":"Patch `sparsify/config.py` and `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` so `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is recognized by validation and architecture dispatch, then rerun the same proxy experiment at `K=32, EF=12` with `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, and `auxk_alpha=0`. This keeps the round focused on a concrete code-fix blocker instead of mixing crash recovery with a new architecture or parameter change.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"run_stability","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the narrowest defensible action after a clear unknown-architecture crash and preserves interpretability by keeping the experiment target fixed. If the repaired run is still weak, that will be a real architecture signal rather than a registration-path artifact.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 101 treats the `bucketed_lowrank_residual` failure as a pure implementation blocker: the runtime reported `Unknown architecture: 'bucketed_lowrank_residual'`.","The follow-up keeps the architecture and low-K target fixed and only repairs config validation/factory registration so the family can actually instantiate.","Do not draw any architecture conclusion from round 100 until the repaired registration path has been tested on the same `K=32, EF=12` proxy setup."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `bucketed_lowrank_residual` run is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and map it to `K=40, EF=12` before any EF work.","If the repaired run completes but is clearly weak, archive stale weak incubating families and pivot the next move toward a stronger objective-level reformulation rather than another architecture-local tweak."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0073.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` at the refreshed low-K mainline target (`K=32`, `EF=12`) remained weak, so the next informative move is to keep that lower-K target fixed and test a different architecture that changes the access pattern itself. Run `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to check whether grouped residual competition yields a better low-K quality/deployment tradeoff than the recent routed and two-stage variants.","summary":"Hold the refreshed comparison target at `K=32`, `EF=12` and switch only architecture to `lowrank_grouped_residual`. This continues the stagnation-breaking search with a more structured low-K mechanism rather than another TopK-local or optimizer change.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round architecture-led under severe stagnation and preserves the lower-K mainline target introduced in rounds 71-72. The main risk is that the grouped residual idea was only middling at `K=40`, `EF=8`, but refreshing it at `K=32`, `EF=12` is a cleaner read than revisiting archived families or resuming minor sweeps.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 73 keeps the refreshed low-K mainline target fixed at `K=32`, `EF=12` and changes only architecture after `two_stage_residual` remained weak.","`lowrank_grouped_residual` is refreshed in the preferred mainline band to test whether more structured grouped competition improves low-K behavior relative to routed and two-stage families."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is still weak, pivot to another fundamentally different non-TopK direction in the same mainline band rather than reopening archived TopK-family comparisons."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0056.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The repeated failure of low-rank residual, batch-global, adaptive-budget, and bucketed routing at `K=40`, `EF=8` suggests the current small-EF lower-K bottleneck may be the hard TopK support mechanism itself rather than routing structure. `jumprelu` is the next fundamentally different same-EF comparison because it changes the sparse activation rule without requiring code edits this round.","summary":"Run a proxy same-EF architecture comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with `ARCHITECTURE=jumprelu`, holding `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed to test whether a different sparse activation mechanism improves the lower-K frontier where several TopK-style small-EF families have failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round on a fundamentally different architecture path under the same lower-K and same-EF comparison target, avoids reopening minor parameter sweeps, and directly tests whether the main failure mode is the TopK mechanism itself. The main risk is that `jumprelu` also underperforms badly at `K=40`, but that would further support that the current small-EF lower-K regime is fundamentally misaligned and may require a broader reformulation rather than more local search.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 55 showed `bucketed_topk` is also weak at `K=40`, `EF=8` (`val_fvu=0.36289801076054573`), so conditional norm-bucket routing does not rescue the current lower-K small-capacity regime.","Next severe-stagnation move is a same-EF comparison with a genuinely different sparse activation mechanism: test `jumprelu` at `K=40`, `EF=8` while holding optimizer and training recipe fixed."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `jumprelu` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak, treat the current `K=40`, `EF=8` search cluster as broadly exhausted and pivot next to a more radical architecture or objective reformulation rather than another minor variant."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0084_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The crash is a pure registration blocker: `residual_vq_topk` is missing from the architecture whitelist in `sparsify/config.py` and likely not wired into the factory path in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`. Patch only that registration path so the unchanged `K=32, EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` proxy can instantiate.","summary":"Apply a narrow registration repair for `residual_vq_topk` inside `sparsify/` and relaunch the exact same proxy target. Do not change the experiment recipe; only make the architecture name legal and constructible by the existing config/factory flow.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Convert the current unknown-architecture crash into a real startup/training signal for the original `residual_vq_topk` target.","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a tight repair scoped directly to the observed `Unknown architecture` error. It preserves the original experiment exactly and avoids mixing in any new search variable.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"residual_vq_topk","K":"32","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 84 repair attempt 1 targets only the concrete registration failure for `residual_vq_topk`; no recipe changes are allowed.","Observed blocker: `ValueError: Unknown architecture: 'residual_vq_topk'` raised in `sparsify/config.py::__post_init__` before training starts.","Keep follow-up repairs, if needed, constrained to making the existing architecture constructible under the unchanged launcher path."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registration repair works and the run completes, evaluate `residual_vq_topk` on quality before any further edits.","If a new concrete constructor or DDP compatibility error appears after registration is fixed, do one more pinpoint repair on the same target.","If the repaired prototype runs and is clearly weak, archive it on quality grounds rather than extending repair work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0085_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The crash is a pure registration blocker: `residual_vq` is missing from the architecture whitelist in `sparsify/config.py` and likely not wired into the constructor dispatch in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`. Patch only that registration path so the unchanged `K=32, EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` proxy can instantiate.","summary":"Apply a narrow registration repair for `residual_vq` inside `sparsify/` and relaunch the exact same proxy target. Do not change the experiment recipe; only make the architecture name legal and constructible by the existing config/factory flow.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Convert the current unknown-architecture crash into a real startup/training signal for the original `residual_vq` target.","family_name":"residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a tight repair scoped directly to the observed `Unknown architecture` error. It preserves the original experiment exactly and avoids mixing in any new search variable.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"residual_vq","K":"32","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/residual_vq.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 85 repair attempt 1 targets only the concrete registration failure for `residual_vq`; no recipe changes are allowed.","Observed blocker: `ValueError: Unknown architecture: 'residual_vq'` raised in `sparsify/config.py::__post_init__` before training starts.","Keep follow-up repairs, if needed, constrained to making the existing architecture constructible under the unchanged launcher path."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registration repair works and the run completes, evaluate `residual_vq` on quality before any further edits.","If a new concrete constructor or DDP compatibility error appears after registration is fixed, do one more pinpoint repair on the same target.","If the repaired prototype runs and is clearly weak, archive it on quality grounds rather than extending repair work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` has now produced a smooth chain of valid lower-K full points through `K=56`, so the remaining high-value question is how much farther this family can extend the Pareto frontier below the old `K=64` anchor before quality bends too sharply. A proxy probe at `K=48` on the unchanged recipe is the cleanest next step to test that lower-K boundary while staying within the strongest validated family and same-EF comparison regime.","summary":"Run a parameter-only proxy experiment for `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=48`, keeping `EF=32`, `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This continues the prioritized lower-K frontier sweep below the new `K=56` point without mixing in architecture or capacity changes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the session on a conservative K-only track instead of pivoting to a new family. That is justified because `K=56` still held up as a real full frontier point, so one more lower-K probe is more informative than reopening EF or architecture immediately. Main risk: `K=48` may regress enough that it only confirms the boundary rather than adding a useful new Pareto point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"48"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 45 full confirmed `K=56` as a valid lower-K frontier point for `lowrank_gated_residual`, so the next informative move is to continue probing the lower-K boundary rather than changing EF.","`K=48` is the next clean same-family, same-EF test below `K=56` to measure whether this family can keep extending the Pareto frontier before architecture search resumes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=48` is promoted and full remains reasonably close to the `K=56` point, keep it as another smaller-K Pareto point and consider one final lower-K probe.","If `K=48` regresses sharply, pivot next to a same-EF architecture comparison or a new family rather than pushing K lower in this family."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0083.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the low-K `lowrank_gated_residual` recovery run at `K=32, EF=12` stayed weak, the next informative move is to switch back to a fundamentally different sparse-allocation mechanism in the same mainline band rather than continue minor tweaks. Run `batch_topk` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe to test whether batch-level support allocation recovers a stronger low-K tradeoff than the recent per-sample and residual-style families.","summary":"Launch a proxy `batch_topk` comparison at `K=32`, `EF=12` using minimal valid env overrides. This keeps K as the priority, preserves same-EF comparability, and satisfies the stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than continuing local tuning on the current best family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"batch_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a real architecture pivot, not another conservative adjustment on `lowrank_gated_residual`. `batch_topk` changes the sparsity mechanism itself while staying within the preferred EF band and the low-K target. Risk: it may still be weak at `K=32`, but that is a cleaner read than extending the stalled residual track with more parameter-only exploitation.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"batch_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 82 restored stability but did not recover competitive low-K quality on `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=32, EF=12`.","The next stagnation-breaking step should be an architecture change in the same EF band, not another local parameter tweak on the current best family.","Keep overrides minimal and launcher-safe for architecture pivots."],"next_hypotheses":["If `batch_topk` at `K=32, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `batch_topk` at `K=32, EF=12` is still weak, pivot to another fundamentally different low-K mechanism rather than returning to more `lowrank_gated_residual` tuning.","If runtime is healthy and quality is materially better than the recent weak low-K pivots but still short of frontier, continue within `batch_topk` by probing the next K point in the same EF band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0057.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `K=40`, `EF=8` search cluster now looks broadly exhausted across low-rank residual, batch/global allocation, adaptive-budget routing, bucketed routing, and JumpReLU, so the next informative move is to test a qualitatively different representation family rather than another sparse-support variant. `codebook_topk` is the strongest remaining same-EF architecture probe because it changes the problem from pure sparse combination to coarse prototype retrieval plus sparse residual correction.","summary":"Run a proxy same-EF architecture comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with `ARCHITECTURE=codebook_topk`, holding `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed to test whether a discrete codebook-plus-residual mechanism can improve the lower-K frontier where the current small-EF sparse families have failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"codebook_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This satisfies the required pivot to a fundamentally different architecture approach, keeps the comparison at the same lower-K and same-EF target, and avoids reopening minor hyperparameter search. The main risk is another clear regression or a policy/runtime rejection, but that result would still narrow the remaining viable search space and clarify whether the current failure is specific to sparse-support mechanisms more broadly.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"codebook_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 56 showed `jumprelu` is also weak at `K=40`, `EF=8` (`val_fvu=0.36313553526997566`), so changing the sparse activation rule alone does not rescue the current lower-K small-capacity regime.","Next severe-stagnation move is a same-EF comparison with a discrete retrieval-style architecture: test `codebook_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` before escalating to more invasive code or objective changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `codebook_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `codebook_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak or rejected, treat the current `K=40`, `EF=8` regime as broadly exhausted and pivot next to a more radical architecture or objective reformulation rather than another nearby variant."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0064.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A lightweight normalization-plus-mixing front end may make the activation space more compatible with very low-K sparse coding, so `preconditioned_topk` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is the next clean same-EF architecture probe to test whether input conditioning improves the low-K frontier where routing-based variants failed.","summary":"Run the newly added `preconditioned_topk` family in proxy at `K=32`, `EF=8` with the shared stable optimizer/LR recipe. This keeps the search on a fundamentally different architecture axis at the prioritized low-K target without changing capacity.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"preconditioned_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This preserves the stagnation-driven architecture pivot and finally gets a real signal for the newly added preprocessing-oriented family. The main risk is that conditioning-only changes may still be too weak, but it is the least-bad informative move before another broader pivot.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"preconditioned_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 64 executes the newly introduced `preconditioned_topk` family at the prioritized low-K target instead of opening another architecture branch immediately.","This is a same-EF `K=32`, `EF=8` preprocessing-oriented comparison meant to test coordinate conditioning rather than routing or residual structure.","If `preconditioned_topk` runs cleanly and is weak, treat preprocessing-only fixes as another negative result in the current small-EF low-K band and pivot again rather than increasing EF."],"next_hypotheses":["If `preconditioned_topk` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is promising, keep the family fixed and compare a nearby K such as `K=40` before touching EF.","If `preconditioned_topk` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is weak, pivot to another fundamentally different low-K mechanism, likely a mixture-style or output-aware direction, rather than increasing expansion factor."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0086.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery mode rules out further architecture/code changes, so the next stability-first move is to stay on the best working family and make one conservative parameter-only adjustment that remains low-K focused: raise `lowrank_gated_residual` from `K=32` to `K=40` at `EF=12` with the same stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe to see whether a small K increase restores a usable signal without abandoning the low-K regime.","summary":"Launch a proxy recovery run on `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40, EF=12` using the unchanged stable recipe. This keeps the round strictly param-only, uses the current best working configuration, and prioritizes stability while staying near the low-K target band.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Recover a clean, more informative low-K baseline in the preferred EF band with lower crash risk than another new-family attempt.","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This obeys crash recovery constraints and changes only one conservative dimension on the strongest known working family. It is not a frontier-seeking move, but it is the safest way to restore signal after consecutive crashes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"lowrank_gated_residual","K":"40","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 86 enters crash recovery mode, so architecture pivots and code edits are temporarily suspended in favor of stability-only param sweeps on `lowrank_gated_residual`.","Use `lowrank_gated_residual` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe as the recovery anchor while recent prototype families are crashing on registration.","A small K increase from 32 to 40 at `EF=12` is the chosen recovery step because it stays low-K while reducing risk relative to repeated fresh prototype attempts."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40, EF=12` runs cleanly and improves materially over the `K=32, EF=12` recovery result, map `K=48` next before touching other parameters.","If it runs cleanly but remains weak, keep recovery discipline and try one more conservative same-family adjustment rather than reopening code edits immediately.","If it still crashes despite the stable family and recipe, reduce risk further with another minimal same-family recovery step on the same EF band."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0077.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After 27 no-improve rounds and 13 rounds without a new family, the least-bad informative move is a real low-K architecture pivot: run `multi_branch_gated` at `K=32`, `EF=16` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe to test whether branch-specialized gated routing preserves more quality than the current low-K residual families under the required `EF<=16` regime.","summary":"Launch a proxy `multi_branch_gated` comparison at `K=32`, `EF=16` using only minimal valid env overrides. This satisfies the stagnation policy by switching to a fundamentally different architecture, respects the K-priority and EF<=16 constraints, and targets a potentially non-dominated low-K point rather than another local tweak.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"multi_branch_gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is intentionally not another LR/EF micro-tune on `lowrank_gated_residual`. `multi_branch_gated` already showed competitive proxy signal at `K=128, EF=16`, so the most informative next step is to test whether its specialization mechanism survives at the prioritized low-K target. Risk: it may collapse at `K=32`, but that failure would still cleanly falsify a strategically distinct family under the current policy constraints.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"multi_branch_gated"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation and 13 rounds without a new family justify a genuine architecture pivot rather than more local tuning.","`multi_branch_gated` had promising prior proxy signal at `K=128, EF=16` and is the strongest unexhausted distinct family to test at low K.","Keep env overrides minimal; avoid nonessential metadata keys in the launcher payload."],"next_hypotheses":["If `multi_branch_gated` at `K=32, EF=16` is competitive, map `K=40` on the same family before touching EF.","If it runs but is clearly weak, archive this low-K branch-specialization direction and pivot to another fundamentally different family rather than returning to micro-tuning.","If runtime shows a perf regression with decent quality, follow with a narrow performance-code pass instead of concluding the architecture is bad."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0093_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The round 93 crash was a pure implementation gap: `two_code_residual_vq` was missing from architecture validation and SAE factory dispatch. Registering the architecture and adding a minimal runnable two-code residual-VQ sparse coder under `sparsify/` should unblock the original `K=40, EF=12` proxy experiment without changing its intended design.","summary":"Patched the existing experiment target so `two_code_residual_vq` can instantiate and train: added the architecture to config validation, wired factory dispatch, and implemented a minimal `TwoCodeResidualVQSparseCoder` that composes two hard codebook selections before sparse residual correction. Local smoke test passed for config validation, factory lookup, forward, and backward.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"unblock_run","family_name":"two_code_residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"Kept the repair scoped to `sparsify/` and preserved the original experiment target and env overrides. Verified the new class on a local instantiate/forward/backward smoke test; the next likely blocker, if any, would be a deeper training-time issue rather than the previous unknown-architecture crash.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_code_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 93 repair attempt 1 fixed a concrete registration blocker for `two_code_residual_vq` under `sparsify/` only.","Added `two_code_residual_vq` to `TrainConfig` architecture validation and `_get_sae_class` dispatch.","Implemented a minimal runnable `TwoCodeResidualVQSparseCoder` by extending the existing residual-VQ pattern with a second hard codebook/router stage before sparse residual coding.","Local smoke test passed: config validation, factory dispatch, forward, and backward all succeeded for `architecture=two_code_residual_vq`, `k=40`, `expansion_factor=12`."],"next_hypotheses":["Re-run the original round 93 proxy target unchanged now that the unknown-architecture crash is repaired.","If the next run crashes again, keep the experiment fixed and patch only the concrete new traceback in `sparsify/` as repair attempt 2.","If the run completes, judge `two_code_residual_vq` on low-K quality at the exact `(K=40, EF=12)` comparison point before any further architecture work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0082.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery mode rules out further code changes, so the next stability-first move is to return to the strongest working family and make one conservative parameter-only adjustment that still respects the low-K priority: run `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe to get a clean low-K signal in the preferred EF band.","summary":"Launch a proxy `lowrank_gated_residual` recovery run at `K=32`, `EF=12` using the known stable training recipe and no code edits. This keeps the round strictly param-only, uses the current best working family, stays within the preferred EF band, and prioritizes lower K while focusing on stability.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This follows crash-recovery constraints exactly: no code edits, no new family, and only a minor parameter move on the strongest validated architecture. The main risk is that `K=32, EF=12` still trails the EF32 frontier, but recovery mode prioritizes a stable, interpretable signal over broader exploration.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash recovery mode forced a param-only round on the best working family rather than another architecture pivot.","Use `lowrank_gated_residual` as the stability anchor during consecutive-crash recovery; keep the optimizer and LR recipe fixed unless stability evidence fails.","This round restores a legal EF<=16 comparison while still honoring the low-K priority."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` runs cleanly and is competitive, map `K=40` at the same EF before touching other parameters.","If it runs cleanly but remains weak, keep recovery mode discipline and use one more minor parameter-only adjustment on the same family rather than reopening code edits immediately.","If it crashes despite the stable family and recipe, reduce risk further with another conservative parameter-only recovery step on the same family."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0014.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Stagnation and the runtime policy both point to exploitation on the current best family rather than another architecture change. The strongest clean next move is to keep the winning `two_stage_residual` K=128 / EF=16 / signum / aux-free recipe fixed and lower only the learning rate to `4e-4`, testing whether the current plateau is partly an optimization-step-size issue after the family-specific stage allocation stabilized.","summary":"Run a proxy sweep point for `two_stage_residual` at K=128 with `LR=4e-4`, holding the rest of the best recipe fixed (`ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=16`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This is a one-variable exploitation pass aligned with the policy's prescribed untested LR set.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the explicit exploitation guidance, keeps variable isolation clean, and avoids another architecture detour after three no-improve rounds. The main risk is that `4e-4` is simply too conservative and under-trains relative to `1.6e-3`, but it is still the least noisy informative sweep point among the remaining untested LRs.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round proposal stays in exploitation mode on `two_stage_residual` and changes only LR.","Use `LR=4e-4` as the next untested midpoint-down step below the current best `1.6e-3` while keeping the aux-free EF=16 K=128 anchor fixed."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=4e-4` improves proxy FVU, promote and then continue LR stabilization before changing another parameter.","If `LR=4e-4` regresses, test the remaining prescribed LR extremes (`2e-4` or `3.2e-3`) one at a time before revisiting aux or EF.","If LR sweep stays flat across the prescribed points, move to the next one-variable exploitation axis on this family, likely `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01`."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0027.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` remains the best full-signal family, but the recent `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` and `LR=1.2e-3` probes both regressed at the K=128 anchor, so the optimization-side local moves look weak. The next clean single-variable stabilization move is to increase `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 32 to 48 at K=128 while keeping the winning signum/LR/aux recipe fixed, testing whether the gated residual selector is now capacity-limited rather than optimization-limited.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=128 with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=48`, holding signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed. This checks whether extra residual dictionary capacity can push anchor quality lower after the recent aux and LR sweeps both regressed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one primary variable, `expansion_factor`, and follows directly from two failed optimization-side probes by testing a different stabilization axis. It is a better next move than more LR/aux retuning because it asks whether the current mainline family has simply saturated its residual capacity at EF=32.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"48"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 27 tests whether `lowrank_gated_residual` is capacity-limited at the K=128 anchor after `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` and `LR=1.2e-3` both regressed.","This is the first family-internal expansion-factor sweep for `lowrank_gated_residual`; the family had previously captured the frontier at EF=32 across K={32,64,128}."],"next_hypotheses":["If `EXPANSION_FACTOR=48` improves proxy FVU at K=128, promote it to full and then test whether the higher-capacity recipe also helps K=64.","If `EXPANSION_FACTOR=48` is flat or worse, keep EF=32 as the family default and consider a different single-variable stabilization move such as a mild LR increase.","If quality improves but runtime or memory is flagged as regressed, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass instead of discarding the higher-capacity recipe."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0069.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After 19 no-improve rounds, continue the stagnation break with a genuinely different sparse mechanism while keeping the comparison target fixed. Run `batch_topk` at `K=48`, `EF=16` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to test whether batch-level support allocation preserves more quality than the recent low-rank residual variants at the same lower-K operating point.","summary":"Probe a fundamentally different architecture at the same `K=48`, `EF=16` target used in the last round. This keeps lower-K pressure active and isolates architecture more cleanly than another family-local sweep.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality_improve","family_name":"batch_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture approach and avoids another minor tweak. The main risk is that `batch_topk` also collapses at low K, but using the same `K=48`, `EF=16`, optimizer, and LR as the recent comparison keeps the read cleaner than reopening EF or optimizer axes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"batch_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"48"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 69 returns to strict variable isolation after the round-68 warning by keeping `K=48`, `EF=16`, optimizer, and LR fixed and changing only architecture.","`batch_topk` is the next fundamentally different low-K mechanism to test in the preferred mainline band because its earlier signal was materially better than other non-residual alternatives before the weak `EF=8` low-K comparison cluster."],"next_hypotheses":["If `batch_topk` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is competitive, continue the same family downward to `K=40` before touching EF.","If `batch_topk` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is clearly weak, pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism such as `bucketed_topk` or `routed` in the same mainline EF band rather than returning to more lowrank-family tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After eight straight no-improve rounds and with gated already mapped at K=32/64/128, the least-bad informative move is a fundamentally different architecture that changes the input geometry rather than doing another local sweep. A `whitened_topk` proxy run at K=128 under the current strongest gated recipe can test whether a learned input preconditioner makes the activation space easier to sparsify and opens a new quality frontier without coupling in optimizer or K changes.","summary":"Run a `whitened_topk` proxy comparison at K=128, keeping the current best signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe fixed and changing only architecture.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"whitened_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the stagnation policy by trying a new architecture family instead of another minor gated tweak. Risk: the current `whitened_topk` implementation is only a shallow learned preconditioner and may add compute without enough representational benefit, but proxy is the correct tier for that read.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation with gated already explored at K=32/64/128 triggered a new-family architecture probe rather than more local tuning.","This round tests input-space preconditioning as the main variable via `whitened_topk`, holding the current best optimization recipe fixed."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_topk` is materially better than recent non-gated alternatives, keep incubating it with a family-specific stabilization pass before any full request.","If `whitened_topk` is clearly uncompetitive, pivot to another genuinely different architecture mechanism rather than returning to minor gated parameter sweeps.","If quality looks promising but runtime is abnormally slow, follow with an `edit_perf_code` round instead of discarding the family on architecture grounds."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0079.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After low-K routing, branch-specialized gating, adaptive-budget, and input-preconditioning pivots all stayed clearly weak, the next informative move is to change the sparsity mechanism itself and refresh a previously promising non-TopK baseline in the preferred mainline band: run `jumprelu` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe to test whether thresholded sparse activation recovers a viable low-K tradeoff where recent low-K family pivots failed.","summary":"Launch a proxy `jumprelu` comparison at `K=32`, `EF=12` using only minimal valid env overrides. This keeps K as the top priority, stays in the preferred EF band, and tries a fundamentally different sparse activation mechanism rather than another local tweak or another residual/routing variant.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a genuine architecture pivot, not a parameter sweep. `jumprelu` had earlier positive signal but has not been refreshed in the current low-K, EF<=16 mainline regime, so this is more informative than repeating recently weak families. Risk: it may still be uncompetitive at `K=32`, but that cleanly tests whether the current stagnation is partly caused by overcommitting to residual/routing-style families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`whitened_topk` at `K=32, EF=12` was catastrophically weak, so low-K input-preconditioning-only approaches should not be the next local tuning target.","The next stagnation-breaking move should change the sparse activation mechanism itself rather than adding more routing or preprocessing structure.","Keep env overrides minimal and launcher-safe; avoid nonessential metadata keys."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` at `K=32, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `jumprelu` at `K=32, EF=12` is still weak, pivot to another fundamentally different family such as a discrete/codebook-style residual direction rather than returning to residual/routing micro-tuning.","If runtime is healthy and quality is materially better than recent weak low-K families but still short of frontier, keep the same family and test `K=40` as the next single-variable move."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0055.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current lower-K small-EF regime appears to fail not only for residual and budget-allocation variants but also for batch-global selection, so the next informative move is to test conditional specialization rather than another global sparse mechanism. `bucketed_topk` may recover quality at `K=40`, `EF=8` by routing examples into simpler norm-conditioned subdictionaries before TopK selection.","summary":"Run a proxy same-EF architecture comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with `ARCHITECTURE=bucketed_topk`, holding `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed to test whether norm-bucketed conditional dictionaries improve the lower-K frontier where the current small-EF families have failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This continues the required stagnation pivot toward fundamentally different architecture mechanisms, keeps the experiment at the same lower-K and same-EF target, and avoids reopening minor hyperparameter work. The main risk is another clear regression, but that would still meaningfully narrow the search by ruling out a conditional-dictionary path at the current comparison point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 54 showed `adaptive_budget_topk` is also extremely weak at `K=40`, `EF=8` (`val_fvu=0.42443543300032616`), so relaxing fixed per-sample budget alone does not rescue the current lower-K small-capacity regime.","Next severe-stagnation move is another same-EF architecture comparison with a different conditionalization mechanism: test `bucketed_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` before considering more exotic or code-changing directions."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `bucketed_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak, pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism at the same target, such as `jumprelu`, rather than resuming local sweeps on the current families."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0087.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At low K, the residual after the low-rank trunk is likely still poorly conditioned at `EF=12`, so support selection is wasting budget on scale/correlation artifacts. A new `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual` family that RMS-centers and lightly mixes the residual before gated top-k selection may improve same-`(K=40, EF=12)` FVU over the discarded `lowrank_gated_residual` local baseline without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Added a new prototype architecture, `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual`, under `sparsify/` and registered it in config/class dispatch. The family keeps the proven low-rank trunk, but preconditions the residual with per-sample centering, RMS normalization, a small rolled mix, and a light learned low-rank correction before gated support selection. A local forward/backward smoke test passed, so the next move is a proxy run at the active comparison point `K=40, EF=12` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3` recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"whitened_lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This stays within the edit budget, respects the EF<=16 cap, and makes one architecture-only change at the same `(K, EF)` local comparison point. The main risk is that whitening-like conditioning could misalign encoder scores with the unchanged decoder basis, so this should be treated as an informative prototype rather than a presumed win.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 87 introduces `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual`, a low-K prototype that keeps the low-rank trunk but preconditions the residual before gated support selection.","The prototype was wired into config validation and class dispatch, and a local forward/backward smoke test succeeded."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40, EF=12` runs cleanly and beats the local `lowrank_gated_residual` baseline, compare the same family at `K=32, EF=12` to test whether conditioning helps recover lower-K quality.","If it runs cleanly but is weak, keep the space-first direction alive only if diagnostics suggest healthier support usage; otherwise pivot to a more structurally different low-K family rather than more minor gating tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0043.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` has already shown that quality degrades smoothly between `K=128` and `K=64`, with the new `K=96` point landing much closer to the anchor than to the lower-K regime. A proxy run at `K=80` on the same proven recipe is the cleanest next Pareto probe: it prioritizes lower-K exploration, keeps expansion factor fixed for a fair within-family comparison, and can reveal a new non-dominated tradeoff between the existing `K=64` and `K=96` frontier points.","summary":"Run a parameter-only proxy experiment for `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=80`, holding the current best recipe fixed (`EF=32`, `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This targets the highest-value open gap on the K frontier without mixing in architecture or capacity changes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is intentionally conservative: it does not open a new family even though architecture exploration remains broadly allowed. That is justified here because operator hints put K reduction first, `K=80` is still untested, and the recent `K=96` result provides a strong local signal that an intermediate lower-K point could extend the frontier. Main risk: the result may simply interpolate between existing points without becoming non-dominated.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"80"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 42 established `K=96` as a real frontier point for `lowrank_gated_residual`, so the most informative next K-only follow-up is to fill the open gap below it rather than reopen anchor tuning.","`K=80` is currently untested in the recorded history and is a fair same-EF within-family comparison point between the existing `K=64` and `K=96` frontier results."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=80` is promoted and lands close to the `K=96` quality level, promote it to full as a likely new non-dominated Pareto point.","If `K=80` falls back toward the `K=64` regime, continue K exploration with one lower nearby point such as `K=72` rather than shifting to EF tuning."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0102.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`bucketed_lowrank_residual` produced the strongest exact-neighborhood result seen so far at `K=32, EF=12`, so the next informative move is to keep the family fixed and map it to the adjacent low-K point `K=40` before any EF work. This preserves same-EF fairness, prioritizes K-lane coverage, and tests whether the conditional residual-dictionary reformulation remains competitive beyond a single low-K point.","summary":"Run a proxy `bucketed_lowrank_residual` comparison at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This is the cleanest follow-up to the repaired family because it stays in the active low-K tradeoff lane, uses the same EF band, and extends the only recent architecture signal that materially beat the local alternatives at `K=32`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a single-variable continuation of the only recent family with a strong low-K signal in the active lane. The main risk is that the gain is specific to `K=32`, but mapping to `K=40` is still the most informative next step before concluding whether the family deserves sustained incubation.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 102 keeps `bucketed_lowrank_residual` fixed and maps it from `K=32` to `K=40` at the same `EF=12` band after the repaired family produced the strongest local low-K result so far.","This is a same-EF K-mapping follow-up, not a cross-capacity claim, and it directly tests whether the family can strengthen the low-K tradeoff lane beyond a single point.","If the family regresses sharply at `K=40`, the apparent `K=32` win may be narrow; if it remains strong, it becomes a real conditional-dictionary candidate for the lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=40, EF=12`, judge whether it deserves continued incubation or promotion as the current low-K mainline candidate.","If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` regresses badly at `K=40, EF=12`, archive the family and pivot next toward a stronger objective-level reformulation rather than another local architecture tweak."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0045.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` still yields valid non-dominated frontier points as K decreases, but the new `K=72` full result is now nearing the `K=64` quality regime. The most informative K-first follow-up is a lower boundary probe at `K=56` on the unchanged recipe, which tests whether the family can still produce a worthwhile smaller-K tradeoff below the current `K=64` point before switching effort back to architecture exploration.","summary":"Run a parameter-only proxy experiment for `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=56`, holding the current best recipe fixed (`EF=32`, `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This extends the prioritized lower-K sweep below the current frontier and avoids mixing in EF or architecture changes while the remaining open question is the lower-K boundary.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This remains a conservative within-family K probe rather than a new-family step. That is warranted because lower-K exploration still has explicit priority, `K=72` did not collapse enough to close the track, and a single sharper boundary check at `K=56` is more informative than reopening EF tuning. Main risk: the result may regress enough to add little beyond confirming that this family’s practical frontier bends sharply below `K=64`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"56"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 44 full showed `K=72` remains non-dominated but is approaching the existing `K=64` regime, so the next informative K-first move is a sharper lower boundary test rather than more interpolation near 80.","`K=56` is an untested same-family, same-EF probe that directly measures whether `lowrank_gated_residual` can keep extending the Pareto frontier below `K=64` before architecture search resumes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=56` is competitive enough to promote, run full to determine whether it creates a new smaller-K Pareto point below `K=64`.","If `K=56` regresses clearly past the useful frontier range, pivot next to a same-EF architecture comparison or a new family rather than continuing this K sweep."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0012.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`multi_branch_gated` produced the strongest new non-winning proxy signal since `two_stage_residual`, so the next informative move is a family-specific stabilization pass rather than pivoting away immediately. Increasing `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at K=128 tests whether the multi-branch gated encoder is capacity-limited under the current strong signum recipe and can close more of the remaining quality gap without changing architecture or optimization.","summary":"Run a `multi_branch_gated` proxy stabilization pass at K=128 with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, keeping the current signum/aux-free recipe fixed and changing only expansion factor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality_improve","family_name":"multi_branch_gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the new family after a genuinely competitive prototype result and changes only one generic variable on the same architecture. Risk: the prototype may not be width-limited and EF=32 may regress or add cost, but this is the cleanest first stabilization probe before considering promotion or broader family-local changes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"multi_branch_gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`multi_branch_gated` prototype at K=128 reached proxy FVU 0.15793968923389912, making it a competitive incubating family worth stabilization rather than immediate discard.","This round tests whether the new family is capacity-limited by increasing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at the K=128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `multi_branch_gated` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improves materially, promote it to full and continue stabilizing the family.","If EF=32 is flat or worse, test a family-specific branch-allocation or branch-count parameter next rather than continuing generic width sweeps.","If quality is promising but runtime regresses materially, follow with a targeted performance-focused code pass."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0074.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_grouped_residual` at the refreshed low-K target (`K=32`, `EF=12`) improved over the recent weak non-TopK probes but remained far from competitive, so the next informative move is a same-target comparison against the strongest simpler non-gated baseline family. Run `lowrank_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to test whether the grouped routing machinery is hurting low-K quality relative to a cleaner low-rank residual path in the preferred mainline band.","summary":"Keep the refreshed comparison target fixed at `K=32`, `EF=12` and switch only architecture to `lowrank_residual`. This continues the stagnation-breaking architecture search while prioritizing lower K and a fair same-EF comparison.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality_improve","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This preserves the lower-K mainline target and changes only architecture after the grouped residual refresh remained clearly behind the frontier. The main risk is limited novelty because `lowrank_residual` already has positive evidence at other K/EF points, but that is also why it is the strongest clean comparator for isolating whether extra routing structure is helping or hurting at `K=32`, `EF=12`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 74 keeps the refreshed low-K mainline target fixed at `K=32`, `EF=12` and switches only architecture from `lowrank_grouped_residual` to `lowrank_residual`.","This same-EF comparison directly tests whether grouped/routed structure is the source of recent low-K weakness relative to a simpler low-rank residual family with real prior signal."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `lowrank_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is still weak, pivot to another fundamentally different non-TopK direction in the same mainline band rather than reopening archived TopK-family comparisons."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0044.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` continues to produce smooth, non-dominated tradeoffs as K is reduced, and the new `K=80` full point now cleanly fills the gap between `K=64` and `K=96`. The next highest-value K-only probe is `K=72` on the same recipe, which directly tests whether the frontier can be pushed further downward in K while staying materially above the `K=64` quality floor.","summary":"Run a parameter-only proxy experiment for `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=72`, holding the current best recipe fixed (`EF=32`, `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This continues the prioritized lower-K Pareto mapping and avoids reopening EF or architecture while a strong within-family K frontier remains active.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is another conservative K-frontier interpolation rather than a new-family step. That is justified because the runtime guidance explicitly prioritizes lower K over EF, the same-EF mainline family is still yielding useful non-dominated points, and `K=72` is the cleanest next informative move after `K=80` held up in full. Main risk: the result may collapse toward the existing `K=64` regime and add little beyond confirming the local slope.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"72"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 43 full confirmed `K=80` as a real intermediate frontier point for `lowrank_gated_residual`, strengthening the case for a denser local K sweep below 80 before any EF change.","`K=72` is the next clean same-family, same-EF probe to test how far the current lowrank_gated_residual frontier can be extended toward smaller K without reopening architecture search."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=72` is promoted and remains clearly above the `K=64` quality level, promote it to full as another likely non-dominated Pareto point.","If `K=72` falls close to the existing `K=64` regime, continue one more lower-K boundary check at `K=56` or pivot to a new same-EF architecture comparison rather than expanding EF."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0088.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The whitening-style residual preconditioning direction is weak at the active `(K=40, EF=12)` point, so the next informative move is a genuinely different low-K mechanism: add a minimal `residual_vq` prototype that uses a hard coarse codebook assignment plus a sparse residual correction. If low-K quality is limited by continuous support selection rather than pure capacity, this discrete-first representation should be a better fit at `K=32, EF=12` than the current low-rank gated residual family.","summary":"Implement a runnable `residual_vq` architecture under `sparsify/` and launch its first real proxy comparison at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This keeps the round focused on one architecture change, stays in the preferred EF band, and prioritizes lower-K exploration with a fundamentally different representation family instead of another local tweak.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture and also respects the crash-repair guidance by turning the previously blocked `residual_vq` direction into a real minimal prototype. The main risk is that a hard codebook path may still underperform badly at the first attempt, but that outcome would be more informative than another same-family residual-gating variant.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 88 pivots away from the weak whitened residual-gating probe and reopens the discrete representation branch with a minimal runnable `residual_vq` prototype at low K.","The target comparison is `K=32, EF=12` so the first residual-VQ signal is gathered directly in the low-K tradeoff lane rather than at a larger K or larger EF."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq` at `K=32, EF=12` runs and is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40, EF=12` before touching EF.","If it runs cleanly but is clearly weak, archive the family on quality grounds and pivot to another structurally different low-K direction rather than more gating or whitening tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0026.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` clearly regressed proxy quality for `lowrank_gated_residual` at the K=128 anchor, so the family default should stay at `AUXK_ALPHA=0`. The next clean single-variable stabilization move is to lower LR slightly from `1.6e-3` to `1.2e-3` at K=128, testing whether the gated residual mainline is overshooting near convergence and can realize a modest quality gain through a narrower optimization step without changing architecture, K, or aux behavior.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=128 with `LR=1.2e-3`, holding EF=32, signum, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed. This probes whether a modest LR reduction improves the anchor-point quality of the current leading family after the aux sweep regressed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one primary variable, `lr`, and follows directly from the failed aux experiment by reverting to the known-good family default. A small downward LR move is the least-coupled next optimization test for the current mainline family and is more informative than reopening architecture search immediately.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 26 reverts `lowrank_gated_residual` to the known-good `AUXK_ALPHA=0` default after the `0.01` aux trial regressed badly at K=128 proxy.","This round tests a narrow LR reduction at the K=128 anchor to see whether the current mainline family benefits from a less aggressive signum step size."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.2e-3` improves proxy FVU at K=128, promote it to full and then test the same LR at K=64 before broader sweeps.","If `LR=1.2e-3` is flat or worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the family default and consider a different single-variable stabilization move such as a mild LR increase or expansion-factor change.","If proxy quality is promising but runtime is flagged as a perf regression, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass rather than attributing the result to architecture quality."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0040.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The search has already covered multiple K values on the best mainline and recent continuous-support pivots have all underperformed, so the next informative step is to actually benchmark the newly added discrete additive family rather than return to more tuning. `product_codebook_topk` tests whether representing coarse structure with multiple retrieved codewords before a sparse residual correction can break the current fixed-TopK quality ceiling.","summary":"Run the first proxy benchmark for `product_codebook_topk` at K=128 under the current strong shared recipe. This keeps the round architecture-only, turns the new family from code into measured signal, and directly tests the discrete additive-codebook direction before deciding whether to promote or archive it.","change_type":"architecture_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Best case: proxy FVU lands materially below recent alternative families like `batch_topk` and `bucketed_topk`, ideally approaching the low-0.14s or better. Failure case: discrete additive codebooks also miss badly, letting us archive this branch and pivot away from codebook-style sparse search.","family_name":"product_codebook_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This round preserves single-variable isolation by evaluating the newly introduced family without adding optimizer or LR changes. It follows the stagnation rule by continuing the architecture pivot instead of resuming low-signal parameter sweeps.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"product_codebook_topk","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"32","K":"128","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0.0","DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD":"10000000","USE_HADAMARD":"0","BATCH_SIZE":"1","GRAD_ACC_STEPS":"8","MICRO_ACC_STEPS":"1","HOOKPOINTS":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 40 is the first actual proxy evaluation for `product_codebook_topk` after the family was added in round 39.","This run is meant to validate whether discrete additive codewords plus sparse residual correction produce any real quality signal, not to tune the family locally.","If this proxy is uncompetitive, codebook-style additive routing should be treated as another failed architecture branch and deprioritized."],"next_hypotheses":["If `product_codebook_topk` is competitive at K=128 proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `product_codebook_topk` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow `code_fix` on codeword lookup or routing rather than discarding the family.","If `product_codebook_topk` remains clearly behind, archive additive product-codebook routing and pivot to a fundamentally different direction such as input-space preprocessing or output-aware objectives rather than another sparse-allocation variant."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0015.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The downward LR sweep regressed at `4e-4`, so the next clean exploitation move is to test the opposite remaining LR extreme on the current best `two_stage_residual` recipe. Increasing only the learning rate to `3.2e-3` may recover or improve optimization efficiency at K=128 if the family is currently slightly under-stepping around the `1.6e-3` anchor.","summary":"Run a proxy `two_stage_residual` sweep at K=128 with `LR=3.2e-3`, keeping the winning EF=16, signum, aux-free configuration fixed. This continues the prescribed one-parameter LR sweep after the `4e-4` regression.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays inside the mandated exploitation sweep, isolates one variable, and uses the most informative remaining LR point after the low-LR regression. The main risk is optimizer instability or overshooting at `3.2e-3`, but that is preferable to mixing in aux or architecture changes before the LR axis is exhausted.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 15 continues exploitation on `two_stage_residual` and changes only LR.","After the `LR=4e-4` proxy regression, the next most informative prescribed sweep point is the high-side LR extreme `3.2e-3` on the same aux-free EF=16 K=128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=3.2e-3` improves proxy FVU, promote and then decide whether LR stabilization is sufficient or whether aux should be swept next.","If `LR=3.2e-3` also regresses, finish the LR axis with `LR=2e-4` before moving to `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01`.","If the remaining LR points are uniformly flat or worse, switch the single primary variable to `auxk_alpha` and test `0.01` on the current best `two_stage_residual` recipe."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0095.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`batch_topk` at the exact active point `K=40, EF=12` was decisively weak, so the next informative move is another fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than more residual-family or discrete-trunk tuning. Running `jumprelu` at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe tests whether smoother thresholded support selection recovers low-K quality where routing, residual-VQ, two-code residual-VQ, and batch-budget allocation all failed.","summary":"Run a proxy mainline comparison for `jumprelu` at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged recipe. This stays in the exact active low-K neighborhood, uses the default same-EF comparison band, satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture approach, and reopens a previously archived non-TopK sparsity mechanism instead of creating yet another incubating family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"architecture_signal","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the test fair at the same `(K=40, EF=12)` point and changes only architecture. It also follows the strategic pressure to avoid minor retuning and to prefer a structurally different mechanism while not expanding the incubating-family count further.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 94: `batch_topk` at `K=40, EF=12` was very weak at `0.40311281383037567`, substantially behind the local `lowrank_residual` best `0.17533555254340172`, so the batch-budget hypothesis did not help in the exact low-K neighborhood.","Given the growing incubating set, prefer reopening archived fundamentally different mechanisms with prior signal over starting another brand-new family.","The active low-K point `(K=40, EF=12)` has now rejected routing, two-code residual-VQ, and batch-budget allocation as local winners."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` at `K=40, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=32, EF=12` before touching EF.","If `jumprelu` is also weak at the exact active point, archive stale weak incubating families and consider that the current reconstruction-only search objective may be the flawed direction rather than the sparse mechanism alone.","If several distinct sparse-mechanism probes remain weak at `K=40, EF=12`, refocus the next architecture move on a stronger problem reformulation rather than another local mechanism swap."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0009.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` has established a new K=128 full frontier point, but the sharp K=64 regression suggests the current prototype may be capacity-limited or too brittle outside its initial setting rather than broadly Pareto-dominant yet. The next informative move is a family-specific stabilization pass at the winning K=128 anchor by increasing expansion factor to 32, testing whether more latent capacity lets the staged residual design convert its structural advantage into another quality gain without changing architecture or optimization.","summary":"Run a `two_stage_residual` proxy stabilization pass at K=128 with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, keeping the current signum/aux-free recipe fixed and changing only expansion factor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality_improve","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the winning family rather than abandoning it after one lower-K miss, and it changes exactly one variable on the current best K=128 setup. Risk: the prototype may already be width-saturated and EF=32 may add cost without improving FVU, but this is the cleanest next stabilization read after K=64 regressed sharply.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`two_stage_residual` remained a real K=128 winner in full, but its K=64 proxy run regressed badly to 0.2899633552879095, so lower-K transfer is not automatic for this family.","This round begins family-specific stabilization on the winning K=128 anchor by testing whether extra latent capacity improves the staged residual design at fixed optimization settings."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improves K=128 proxy FVU, promote it to full and continue stabilization around the stronger width.","If EF=32 is flat or worse, test a family-specific sparsity-allocation parameter next rather than continuing generic width sweeps indefinitely.","If quality improves but runtime regresses materially, follow with a targeted performance pass instead of discarding the architecture."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0058_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `K=40`, `EF=8` regime now appears broadly exhausted on quality and `codebook_topk` additionally exposed a concrete distributed-training compatibility failure, so the least-bad next move is a narrow code-fix round rather than another blind architecture swap. Repairing `codebook_topk` so all trainable paths participate in loss is the smallest informative step to determine whether the discrete-retrieval direction is actually bad or was obscured by a DDP-unused-parameter bug.","summary":"Patched `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` so `codebook_topk` uses a straight-through hard routing path for coarse code selection, preserving the original hard code choice in the forward pass while restoring gradients to `code_router.weight` and `code_router.bias`. Local `py_compile` passed and a direct backward check showed nonzero grads on the router parameters, so the original proxy recipe should now run without the prior DDP unused-parameter crash.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Eliminate the training crash and recover a valid proxy FVU for `codebook_topk` at the unchanged `K=40`, `EF=8` target.","family_name":"codebook_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"Kept the fix architecture-local and minimal inside `CodebookTopKSparseCoder._select_code`, without touching launcher, trainer, or experiment settings. Verified syntax and confirmed the previously unused router parameters now receive gradients in a local backward pass.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"codebook_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 repair attempt 1: fixed `codebook_topk` DDP unused-parameter failure in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` by replacing pure `argmax`/`index_select` routing with a straight-through hard assignment over `softmax(code_router(x))` so `code_router.weight` and `code_router.bias` stay in the gradient graph.","Local validation after the patch: `python -m py_compile sparsify/sparse_coder.py` passed, and a direct backward check on `CodebookTopKSparseCoder` produced nonzero grads for `code_router.weight` and `code_router.bias`, matching the suspected root cause from parameter indices 3 and 4 in the crash log."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `codebook_topk` proxy run completes and is competitive, promote it before any family-local tuning.","If the repaired run completes but is clearly weak, treat the current `K=40`, `EF=8` comparison band as broadly exhausted and pivot next to a more radical architecture or objective reformulation rather than another nearby variant.","If the repaired run still crashes, inspect for any remaining architecture-local parameters that are conditionally disconnected under the training loss before changing experiment design."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0023.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` has now earned real full-signal evidence by improving the K=128 frontier over `lowrank_residual`, so the next clean move is to change only K and test whether the same gated residual support mechanism also improves the middle Pareto point. A proxy run at K=64 under the same winning EF=32 signum recipe will show whether this family can expand the frontier beyond the anchor rather than being only a K=128-specific gain.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=64, holding architecture family, EF=32, optimizer, LR, and aux settings fixed. This probes whether the newly promoted family can beat the current full/proxy K=64 `lowrank_residual` point and become the stronger mainline family across K, not just at the anchor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one primary variable, `k`, after a successful K=128 promotion. It is a better frontier-building move than another K=128 local retune because it tests whether the new family generalizes to a smaller, still valuable Pareto point without mixing in architecture or optimizer changes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 23 tests whether `lowrank_gated_residual` generalizes its K=128 gain to the K=64 Pareto point under the same EF=32 signum recipe.","This is the first family-specific stabilization step for `lowrank_gated_residual` after its successful K=128 full promotion."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` improves proxy FVU at K=64, promote it to full and then test K=32 under the same recipe.","If K=64 is flat or worse, keep `lowrank_gated_residual` as a K=128 specialist for now and try a different single-variable stabilization move such as `AUXK_ALPHA` within this family.","If K=64 quality is promising but runtime is flagged as a perf regression, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass instead of discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0094.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current low-K stall suggests the main failure mode may be fixed per-sample top-k allocation rather than trunk capacity alone. Running `batch_topk` at the exact active comparison point `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe is the cleanest fundamentally different architecture test because it changes the sparsity mechanism itself while keeping the same low-K lane and same EF band.","summary":"Run a proxy mainline comparison for `batch_topk` at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged recipe. This stays in the exact active low-K neighborhood, satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a genuinely different architecture approach, and tests whether relaxing fixed per-sample top-k into a batch-level budget improves the local tradeoff where low-rank residual, routed, and two-code residual-VQ have all failed to produce a win.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"architecture_signal","family_name":"batch_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the comparison fair at the same `(K=40, EF=12)` point and changes only the architecture dimension. It avoids EF drift and minor parameter retuning, and it uses a structurally different sparse mechanism rather than another residual-family local tweak.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"batch_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 93 repaired and ran `two_code_residual_vq` at `K=40, EF=12`; it completed cleanly but was weak at `0.24070418253540993`, worse than the local `lowrank_residual` best `0.17533555254340172`.","At the active low-K point `(K=40, EF=12)`, routed and discrete two-code VQ variants are now both clearly behind the local non-gated residual baseline.","After repeated failures from residual-magnitude and discrete-trunk alternatives, the next informative move is to change the sparsity mechanism itself rather than continue same-family tuning or EF changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `batch_topk` at `K=40, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=32, EF=12` before touching EF.","If `batch_topk` is still weak, try another fundamentally different sparsity mechanism such as `jumprelu` at the same `(K=40, EF=12)` point rather than revisiting residual-family tweaks.","If multiple non-TopK sparse-mechanism probes remain weak in the exact low-K neighborhood, the current fixed reconstruction objective may be the flawed search direction rather than capacity or routing details."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0053.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current `lowrank_gated_residual` small-EF track looks exhausted at the lower-K anchor, so the next informative move is a fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than another local tweak. `batch_topk` is the strongest existing non-residual challenger and may preserve more quality at `K=40` by allocating support globally across the batch instead of enforcing rigid per-sample selection.","summary":"Run a proxy same-EF architecture comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with `ARCHITECTURE=batch_topk`, holding `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed to test whether batch-level sparse allocation improves the lower-K Pareto frontier where the current family has stalled.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"batch_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This satisfies the mandatory stagnation pivot away from minor parameter tweaks, keeps the comparison at the current lower-K target, and uses a same-EF architecture check instead of treating larger capacity as a free win. The main risk is that `batch_topk` also degrades sharply at `K=40`, but that negative result would still clarify that the failure mode is broader than the current low-rank residual family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"batch_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe-stagnation pivot: stop minor `lowrank_gated_residual` parameter tweaks and switch to a fundamentally different sparse-allocation mechanism at the same lower-K, same-EF target.","Use `batch_topk` as the next fair lower-K architecture comparison point because it previously showed the strongest proxy signal among the existing non-residual alternative mechanisms and directly tests whether global batch-level support allocation helps at `K=40`, `EF=8`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `batch_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `batch_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is clearly weak, pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism at the same target, such as `adaptive_budget_topk`, rather than resuming local sweeps on `lowrank_gated_residual`."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0021.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improved both K=64 and K=32, so the next clean stabilization move is to complete this capacity sweep at the quality anchor. Increasing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at K=128 may further lower FVU on the best-quality point if the residual branch is still capacity-limited there.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` stabilization pass at `K=128` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, keeping the rest of the winning recipe fixed (`OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This closes the family-specific capacity sweep across the tested K values.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps one variable isolated and follows the strongest available stabilization signal: EF=32 has already helped at lower K, so K=128 is the remaining missing point in the same coherent sweep. The main risk is that K=128 is already saturated at EF=16 and EF=32 only increases cost, but finishing this axis is higher value than switching to aux before the capacity pattern is complete.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 21 completes the `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` stabilization sweep for `lowrank_residual` by testing the remaining anchor at K=128.","Because EF=32 already improved full frontier points at K=32 and K=64, K=128 is the highest-value missing read before moving to a different stabilization axis."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improves proxy FVU at K=128, promote it to full and adopt EF=32 as the likely new family default.","If EF=32 is flat or worse at K=128, keep a mixed frontier with EF=32 for lower K and EF=16 for K=128, then test a different single stabilization axis such as `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01`.","If EF=32 improves K=128 quality but causes clear runtime or memory regression, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code pass rather than discarding the higher-capacity variant outright."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0019.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` now owns the full frontier at K=32, 64, and 128 under the shared EF=16 recipe, so the next clean stabilization move is to test whether a larger sparse residual budget improves quality within this winning family. Increasing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at K=64 may strengthen the middle Pareto point by giving the residual branch more capacity while keeping the low-rank trunk and optimization recipe fixed.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` stabilization pass at `K=64` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, holding the rest of the winning recipe fixed (`OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This tests whether extra residual capacity can further improve the newly established lowrank Pareto frontier at the middle K value.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps variable isolation clean and follows the natural next step after mapping the family across K: stabilize an internal capacity axis on a high-value frontier point. The main risk is that EF=16 is already sufficient and EF=32 only adds cost, but this is the most informative single-parameter read before trying aux or revisiting architecture exploration.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 19 begins family-specific stabilization for `lowrank_residual` after it established full frontier wins at K=32, K=64, and K=128.","The chosen axis is `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, tested at K=64 first because that midpoint best represents whether extra residual capacity improves the practical Pareto frontier rather than only the quality anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improves proxy FVU at K=64, promote it to full and then consider the same capacity increase at K=32 or K=128 depending on where the gain is largest.","If EF=32 is flat or worse, keep EF=16 as the mainline and test a different single stabilization axis such as `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` at K=64 or K=128.","If EF=32 improves quality but causes clear runtime or memory regression, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code pass rather than discarding the higher-capacity variant outright."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0092.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Low-rank residual variants at `K=32` and `K=40` have now converged to near-parity with the local best without producing a real win, so the next informative move is to switch to a fundamentally different sparse-support mechanism at the same low-K comparison point. Running `routed` at `K=40, EF=12` tests whether explicit routing can improve the low-K tradeoff where both gated and non-gated residual magnitude families have stalled.","summary":"Run a proxy mainline comparison for `routed` at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This stays in the exact active low-K lane, uses the same EF band, and satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a genuinely different architecture approach instead of more same-family K mapping.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a clean same-`(K,EF)` architecture comparison against the current local baselines and avoids another weak local tweak. The main risk is that `routed` was weak at `K=32`, but moving to the active `K=40` point is a defensible low-K follow-up for a genuinely different mechanism.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 92 pivots away from further lowrank_residual mapping and tests the fundamentally different `routed` family at the active `K=40, EF=12` comparison point.","This keeps the comparison fair within the same low-K lane and same EF band while checking whether explicit support routing helps where residual-magnitude families have stalled."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed` at `K=40, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and evaluate whether it deserves promotion or a neighboring low-K map before touching EF.","If it remains weak, clear stale incubating families that are no longer competitive and use the freed slot for a new low-K architecture family rather than revisiting more local residual variants."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0004.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Severe stagnation and the policy guidance both point away from more gated-local tuning. The current workspace already contains a `lowrank_residual` implementation that now passes a local forward/backward smoke test, so the least-bad informative move is a clean proxy retry of that fundamentally different family at K=128 under the strongest shared gated recipe. If separating a learned low-rank trunk before TopK makes the residual easier to sparsify, it can lower FVU at fixed K without changing the execution layer.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` comparison at `K=128` using the same strong signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe as the current gated anchor, changing only architecture. No code edit is needed this round because the architecture path already exists and now instantiates successfully.","change_type":"no_change","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I respected the stagnation policy by choosing a fundamentally different architecture rather than another minor sweep. I also kept the round to one primary variable (`architecture`) and avoided unnecessary code edits after verifying the existing `lowrank_residual` path works locally.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Verified in the current workspace that `lowrank_residual` is already registered in `sparsify.config` and `sparsify.sparse_coder`, and a local CPU forward/backward smoke test succeeds.","Given severe stagnation with gated across K={32,64,128}, the next informative move is a clean proxy architecture retry rather than more local hyperparameter tuning."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` shows promising proxy FVU with normal throughput, keep the family incubating and sweep its internal trunk strength with a narrow code edit next.","If `lowrank_residual` runs but shows a throughput regression relative to gated, follow with an `edit_perf_code` round before concluding the family is weak.","If `lowrank_residual` is clearly uncompetitive under the shared strong recipe, pivot to a different fundamentally new family rather than returning to gated-local tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0070.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the weak `batch_topk` result at the fixed lower-K comparison point, the next informative move is another fundamentally different sparse mechanism while holding the target constant. Run `bucketed_topk` at `K=48`, `EF=16` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to test whether simple conditional specialization recovers low-K quality where global batch allocation failed.","summary":"Keep the lower-K comparison point fixed at `K=48`, `EF=16` and switch only architecture from `batch_topk` to `bucketed_topk`. This continues the stagnation-breaking architecture search without reopening EF or optimizer sweeps.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality_improve","family_name":"bucketed_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps primary-variable isolation clean by changing only architecture at the same lower-K target used in the last two rounds. The main risk is that `bucketed_topk` also underperforms at `K=48`, but it is a sufficiently different mechanism to satisfy the stagnation pivot requirement more cleanly than another low-rank-family pass.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"48"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 70 keeps the stagnation-break comparison target fixed at `K=48`, `EF=16` and changes only architecture after `batch_topk` was clearly weak.","`bucketed_topk` is the next mechanism-level comparison because it tests conditional specialization rather than global batch allocation or residual decomposition at the same low-K operating point."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_topk` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is competitive, continue the family downward to `K=40` before touching EF.","If `bucketed_topk` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is clearly weak, pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism such as `routed` in the same mainline band rather than returning to more lowrank-family or TopK-local tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0060.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A low-rank trunk plus group-local winner-take-all residual routing can improve support diversity and regularity at low K, making `K=32` more competitive at the mandated small-capacity setting `EF=8` than the existing low-rank gated residual path.","summary":"Implemented a new `lowrank_grouped_residual` family under `sparsify/`. It reuses the low-rank dense trunk, then applies group-wise local competition before the global `K` selection on the residual branch, targeting better low-K utilization and a more deployment-friendly access pattern. Registered the architecture in config validation and class dispatch. A local instantiate/forward/backward sanity check passed for `architecture=lowrank_grouped_residual`, `EF=8`, `K=32`.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a clean one-variable architecture probe aligned with the stagnation policy. Main risk is that the fixed default `group_topk_size=4` may be suboptimal, but the implementation is minimal, compatible with the existing execution layer, and should produce an interpretable first signal.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 59+ showed severe stagnation and multiple Ks already explored, so this round pivots to a fundamentally different architecture instead of another local sweep.","Added `lowrank_grouped_residual`: low-rank trunk plus grouped residual competition, intended to improve feature diversity and routing regularity specifically for low-K runs.","Local forward/backward sanity passed for `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `EF=8`, `K=32`; if training fails, treat it as an implementation issue rather than an architectural verdict."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=8` shows promising proxy quality or runtime regularity, keep the family fixed and sweep `K` upward slightly (for example `K=40`) before touching EF.","If this grouped residual prototype is clearly weak at `K=32`, `EF=8`, try another fundamentally different low-K mechanism rather than returning to minor tuning on the current gated mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0010.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` remains the best K=128 full architecture, but both the K=64 drop and the EF=32 regression suggest the current 50/50 split of the total K across coarse and residual stages is likely misallocated rather than the family being exhausted. A family-specific stabilization pass that shifts more of the fixed K=128 budget into the first stage should test whether the architecture needs a stronger coarse pass before residual refinement to preserve its K=128 advantage.","summary":"Edit `two_stage_residual` to use a more front-loaded stage-wise K allocation by default, then run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe, changing only that family-specific sparsity-allocation parameter.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality_improve","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the observed failure mode directly: generic width scaling regressed, so the next clean move is a family-specific internal allocation change at the winning anchor rather than abandoning the architecture or doing more generic sweeps. Risk: the default split may not be the bottleneck, but this is the narrowest informative stabilization pass available within the fixed execution layer.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["`two_stage_residual` kept its strong K=128 full win, but both K=64 and EF=32 regressed, pointing to a family-specific allocation issue rather than a simple capacity bottleneck.","This round stabilizes `two_stage_residual` by changing its internal stage-wise K split at the K=128 anchor instead of continuing generic width or lower-K sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If a more front-loaded stage allocation improves K=128 proxy FVU, promote it to full and continue stabilizing this family around the better split.","If the split change is neutral or worse, treat the current prototype as likely overfitting to a narrow configuration and pivot to a different non-gated family rather than continuing blind internal tweaks.","If quality improves but runtime regresses materially, follow with a targeted performance-oriented code pass."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0054.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The failure of both `lowrank_gated_residual` and `batch_topk` at the current lower-K small-EF target suggests the bottleneck may be rigid support allocation rather than just encoder form. `adaptive_budget_topk` is the next fundamentally different mechanism to test at `K=40`, `EF=8`, because it relaxes fixed per-sample allocation while staying in the same fair-capacity comparison band.","summary":"Run a proxy same-EF architecture comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with `ARCHITECTURE=adaptive_budget_topk`, holding `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed to test whether dynamic budget allocation improves the lower-K frontier where both residual and batch-global selection have failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"adaptive_budget_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This continues the mandatory stagnation pivot toward fundamentally different mechanisms, keeps the comparison at the same lower-K and same-EF target, and avoids reopening local hyperparameter sweeps. The main risk is another large regression, but that would still narrow the search by ruling out a second nontrivial allocation mechanism at the current target.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"adaptive_budget_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 53 showed `batch_topk` is extremely weak at `K=40`, `EF=8` (`val_fvu=0.405234944075346`), so batch-global support selection does not rescue the current lower-K small-capacity regime.","Next severe-stagnation move is another same-EF architecture comparison with a fundamentally different allocation mechanism: test `adaptive_budget_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` before considering any return to local tuning."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adaptive_budget_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `adaptive_budget_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak, pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism at the same target, such as `bucketed_topk`, rather than resuming local sweeps on the current families."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0004_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`jumprelu` under the strongest shared recipe remained far behind the gated frontier, so the next non-incremental move is to unblock a genuinely different architecture path rather than keep retuning known families. The `lowrank_residual` family has not produced any quality signal yet because it failed on architecture registration, so a narrow compatibility repair plus a proxy run is the most informative way to test whether removing a shared low-rank trunk before sparse coding can break the current stagnation.","summary":"Repair `lowrank_residual` architecture registration/compatibility under `sparsify/` and run a K=128 proxy comparison on the stable signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"Repair attempt 1 fixed the concrete blocker by registering `lowrank_residual` in config validation and the SAE factory, and by adding a minimal save/load-compatible prototype implementation with successful local config and forward/backward sanity checks. The experiment design, tier, family, and env overrides are unchanged.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 resolved the reported unknown-architecture blocker by adding `lowrank_residual` to config validation and `_get_sae_class`.","A minimal `LowRankResidualSparseCoder` prototype now exists and passed local instantiation plus forward/backward sanity, so the next run should reach training instead of failing at argument parsing."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `lowrank_residual` run now reaches training and yields competitive proxy FVU, keep the family alive for stabilization of the low-rank trunk/residual split.","If a new concrete runtime or sanity error appears, continue repair mode on that specific blocker without changing the experiment target."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0097.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The exact active point `(K=40, EF=12)` has rejected multiple alternative sparsity mechanisms, while `lowrank_residual` remains the strongest same-neighborhood baseline. The new `whitened_lowrank_residual` family was added specifically to test whether residual preconditioning, rather than another sparsity-rule swap, can improve low-K quality at the same `(K, EF)`, so the next informative move is to execute that unchanged proxy comparison before branching further.","summary":"Run the first proxy measurement for `whitened_lowrank_residual` at the exact active low-K comparison point `K=40, EF=12` with the shared `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This is a same-EF, low-K-first architecture comparison against the local `lowrank_residual` baseline and directly follows the round-96 code addition without introducing another new family or parameter sweep.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"whitened_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round focused on a single unresolved architecture question at the exact active lane target. The main risk is that preconditioning helps support selection but not final reconstruction, but running this pending comparison is still more informative than jumping to another family or changing K before the family has any signal at `K=40`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 97 executes the pending first proxy run for `whitened_lowrank_residual` at the exact active comparison point `K=40, EF=12` after the round-96 implementation landed cleanly.","This keeps comparison fairness intact by matching the local `lowrank_residual` baseline on both K and expansion factor rather than using a larger EF to rescue the family.","If the family is competitive here, it earns a direct follow-up at lower K before any EF work; if it is weak, that is evidence against further local residual-preconditioning variants in this lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=40, EF=12`, map the same family to `K=32, EF=12` next before touching EF.","If `whitened_lowrank_residual` is clearly weak under normal runtime, pivot the next architecture move toward a stronger problem reformulation rather than another local sparsity-mechanism or residual-conditioning tweak."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0101_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`bucketed_lowrank_residual` did not fail on quality; it failed on a narrow implementation blocker because the architecture string and runnable class were missing from the `sparsify/` registration path. The correct repair is to register `bucketed_lowrank_residual` in config validation and factory dispatch, provide the minimal runnable sparse coder implementation, and rerun the exact same `K=32, EF=12` proxy target unchanged.","summary":"Patched `sparsify/config.py` and `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` so `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is now recognized by validation and dispatch, and added the missing `BucketedLowRankResidualSparseCoder` implementation. A local instantiation check passed for the exact architecture string, so the same proxy experiment at `K=32, EF=12` with `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, and `auxk_alpha=0` should now be able to run.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"run_stability","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a narrow repair-only follow-up that keeps the original target fixed and addresses the concrete traceback directly. The remaining risk is a deeper runtime or quality issue after registration, but the unknown-architecture blocker itself is now removed.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 for `bucketed_lowrank_residual` fixed the concrete `Unknown architecture` blocker by adding the family to config validation and SAE class dispatch.","The repair also added the missing minimal `BucketedLowRankResidualSparseCoder` implementation so the rerun will not immediately fail on a second missing-class issue.","Local validation and dispatch instantiation passed for `architecture='bucketed_lowrank_residual'` before returning control to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `bucketed_lowrank_residual` run completes and is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and map it to `K=40, EF=12` before any EF work.","If the repaired run completes but is clearly weak, archive stale weak incubating families and pivot the next move toward a stronger objective-level reformulation rather than another architecture-local tweak."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0025.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` now owns the full frontier at K={32,64,128} under the shared EF=32 signum recipe, so the next clean move is a family-internal stabilization step rather than another K sweep. Changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from 0.0 to a small positive value at the K=128 anchor may improve feature utilization and reduce residual support collapse inside the gated selector, potentially lowering FVU further without changing architecture, K, or optimizer.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=128 with `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01`, holding EF=32, signum, LR=1.6e-3, and the rest of the winning recipe fixed. This tests whether a light auxiliary pressure helps the newly promoted mainline family improve anchor-point quality after the full K sweep is complete.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one primary variable, `other_param`, after completing the family's K stabilization sweep. It is a higher-value next step than more K changes because the frontier takeover is already established, and the remaining question is whether the family can push anchor quality lower through better latent utilization.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 25 begins family-internal stabilization for `lowrank_gated_residual` after it captured the full frontier at K={32,64,128}.","This round tests whether a small nonzero `AUXK_ALPHA` helps gated residual feature utilization and improves K=128 quality without changing the established mainline recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` improves proxy FVU at K=128, promote it to full and then test the same aux setting at K=64 before considering broader sweeps.","If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` is flat or worse, keep `AUXK_ALPHA=0` as the family default and try a different single-variable stabilization move such as LR within `lowrank_gated_residual`.","If proxy quality is promising but runtime is flagged as a perf regression, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass rather than treating the aux setting as architecturally bad."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0013.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`multi_branch_gated` showed a competitive prototype signal at K=128, but the strong regression at EF=32 suggests the family is not generically width-limited and instead needs a family-specific routing adjustment. Reducing the number of active branches from the current default to a simpler two-branch mixture should test whether the prototype is over-fragmenting capacity across too many competing branches and can recover better K=128 quality under the same training recipe.","summary":"Edit `multi_branch_gated` to use a simpler two-branch default routing structure, then run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe, changing only that family-specific branch-count parameter.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality_improve","family_name":"multi_branch_gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the family-specific stabilization guidance correctly after the EF=32 regression, and it changes one internal architectural parameter at the same winning anchor rather than continuing generic width sweeps. Risk: branch count may not be the real bottleneck, but it is the narrowest informative next move available within this family.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"multi_branch_gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["`multi_branch_gated` remained competitive at K=128 prototype quality, but increasing `EXPANSION_FACTOR` to 32 regressed badly, indicating the family likely needs a routing/branch-allocation adjustment rather than more generic width.","This round stabilizes `multi_branch_gated` by simplifying the default branch count from three to two at the K=128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If the simpler two-branch `multi_branch_gated` improves materially, continue stabilizing the family and consider promotion to full.","If the branch-count simplification is flat or worse, test a different family-specific routing-weight or branch-allocation change before abandoning the family.","If quality improves but runtime regresses materially, follow with a targeted performance-focused code pass."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0089.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Single-code `residual_vq` is likely too coarse at `K=32, EF=12`, leaving too much residual burden for the sparse correction. A new `two_code_residual_vq` family that composes two hard codebook selections before the same sparse residual stage may recover a better low-K tradeoff by moving more structure into the discrete trunk without raising K or EF.","summary":"Add a new `two_code_residual_vq` prototype under `sparsify/` and run its first proxy comparison at the active low-K target `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This keeps the comparison in the same `(K, EF)` neighborhood while testing a more expressive discrete-first architecture than the weak single-code `residual_vq` baseline.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_code_residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This stays on the mandated architecture-search path, preserves the low-K priority, and uses a same-EF comparison point. The main risk is higher implementation complexity from multi-code routing, but it is still a narrow extension of the discrete residual idea rather than another minor parameter tweak.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_code_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 89 promotes the discrete branch from single-code `residual_vq` to a more expressive `two_code_residual_vq` prototype at the same low-K target.","The comparison remains fixed at `K=32, EF=12` so any gain is attributable to architecture rather than capacity."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_code_residual_vq` at `K=32, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40, EF=12` before touching EF.","If it runs cleanly but remains weak, archive the discrete residual-VQ line for now and pivot to a different low-K family such as mixture routing rather than deeper retuning of this branch."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0018.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` at K=64 established a strong new Pareto point, so the next clean step is to continue the same axis and test whether the family remains non-dominated at K=32. Changing only K from 64 to 32 will determine whether the low-rank trunk continues to preserve enough reconstruction quality to replace the current gated K=32 frontier point.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` comparison at `K=32` with the winning shared recipe held fixed (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=16`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This extends the newly successful family down the Pareto frontier after its full wins at K=128 and K=64.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"pareto_improvement","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps variable isolation clean and follows the strongest available signal: the same family already dominates at K=128 and K=64, so K=32 is the most informative remaining frontier test. The main risk is that quality may collapse at this budget, but that boundary is important to map before switching to family-specific tuning or performance work.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 18 continues the `lowrank_residual` frontier mapping by changing only K from 64 to 32.","Because the family already produced full wins at K=128 and K=64, K=32 is now the highest-value missing frontier point before returning to family-specific stabilization."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` at K=32 is competitive enough to improve the proxy frontier, promote it to full and establish the family as the mainline across all tested K values.","If K=32 regresses too sharply, keep `lowrank_residual` as the K=64/K=128 leader and test a single family-specific stabilization axis at one anchor K, likely expansion factor or aux.","If K=32 is strong but shows runtime or memory regressions, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code pass rather than abandoning the family."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0029.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` remains the best full-signal family, and the exploitation sweep has now shown that moving LR to `1.2e-3` or `3.2e-3`, adding small aux pressure, or increasing EF to 48 all regress the K=128 anchor. The next clean single-variable sweep point is the remaining untested family-specific routing regularization axis from the runtime guidance: increase `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0` to `0.0625` at K=128 while keeping the winning `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, and signum recipe fixed, to test whether only a stronger utilization pressure helps where the weak aux setting failed.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=128 with `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625`, holding `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, and `LR=1.6e-3` fixed. This continues the mandated exploitation sweep by covering the remaining untested aux setting on the current best family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one primary variable, `other_param`, follows the runtime’s explicit exploitation sweep list, and avoids reopening architecture search during stagnation. It is the highest-value next point because the mild aux setting regressed, so the remaining informative question is whether the family needs materially stronger utilization pressure rather than none at all.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0625"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 29 continues exploitation-mode stabilization on `lowrank_gated_residual` by testing the remaining untried aux setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` at the K=128 anchor.","Recent exploitation probes showed regressions for `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01`, `LR=1.2e-3`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=48`, so this round isolates whether only stronger auxiliary pressure can help the current mainline family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` improves proxy FVU at K=128, promote it to full and then test the same aux setting at K=64 before moving to other parameters.","If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` is flat or worse, keep `AUXK_ALPHA=0` as the family default and continue the exploitation sweep with an untested `EXPANSION_FACTOR` point such as `16` or `4`.","If quality improves but runtime is flagged as regressed, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass instead of discarding the higher-aux recipe."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0065.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`preconditioned_topk` did not fail on quality but on architecture registration, so the next informative move is a narrow code-path repair that makes the new family selectable by the existing config/runtime path and then reruns the same `K=32`, `EF=8` probe unchanged.","summary":"Make a minimal `code_fix` for `preconditioned_topk` registration inside `sparsify/` so the runtime recognizes the architecture name, then rerun the same proxy recipe at `K=32`, `EF=8`. This preserves the preprocessing-oriented hypothesis and follows the repair-first rule for clear implementation blockers.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"preconditioned_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the right narrow follow-up because the last round produced no architecture signal at all. The risk is only that registration is not the sole issue, but this is still the smallest coherent repair before deciding whether to abandon the family.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"preconditioned_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 64 produced a pure implementation failure for `preconditioned_topk` (`Unknown architecture`), so this round is a repair-first follow-up rather than a quality verdict.","The repair target is architecture registration/dispatch for `preconditioned_topk` within `sparsify/`, after which the exact same `K=32`, `EF=8` proxy recipe should be rerun for a valid signal.","If the repaired `preconditioned_topk` still crashes, treat the family as blocked by implementation compatibility; if it runs and is weak, record preprocessing-oriented low-K fixes as another negative result in the small-EF band."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `preconditioned_topk` runs and is promising at `K=32`, `EF=8`, keep the family fixed and compare a nearby K such as `K=40` before touching EF.","If the repaired `preconditioned_topk` runs and is weak, pivot to another fundamentally different low-K family, likely a mixture-style or output-aware direction, rather than increasing expansion factor."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0059.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery mode overrides the broader architecture search for this round, so the least-risk move is to stay on the strongest working family and make one minor parameter change that improves stability while preserving lower-K pressure. Running `lowrank_gated_residual` with the same stable `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe at `EF=8` and increasing only `K` from the previously weak `40` to `64` should recover a clean proxy signal in the small-EF regime without reopening code or architecture risk.","summary":"Use a stability-first proxy run on the current best working family by keeping `lowrank_gated_residual`, `EF=8`, `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed and changing only `K` to `64`. This stays within crash-recovery constraints, respects the small-EF guidance, and tests whether the allowed low-capacity regime can produce a valid, less brittle signal before any further architecture exploration.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Recover a stable small-EF proxy measurement on a known working family and determine whether modestly relaxing sparsity from `K=40` to `K=64` meaningfully improves quality in the allowed `EF=8` regime.","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"Kept this round strictly param-only, used a known working architecture, avoided any code edits, and changed only `K` to satisfy crash-recovery and lower-K-first constraints as closely as possible while prioritizing stability.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 59 entered crash-recovery mode, so the round was constrained to `param_only` on a 