research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0072.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`routed` at the refreshed low-K mainline target (`K=32`, `EF=12`) remained weak, so the next informative move is to keep that target fixed and test a different non-TopK architecture family with real prior signal. Run `two_stage_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to see whether coarse-to-fine residual allocation recovers useful low-K quality where explicit routing did not.","summary":"Hold the refreshed low-K comparison point at `K=32`, `EF=12` and switch only architecture from `routed` to `two_stage_residual`. This continues the stagnation-breaking architecture search while preserving the lower-K focus.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round architecture-led under severe stagnation and preserves the lower-K, same-EF target introduced last round. The main risk is that `two_stage_residual` was previously weak at smaller EF, but its prior full-signal evidence makes it a better next non-TopK comparison than reopening archived TopK-style families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 72 keeps the refreshed low-K mainline target fixed at `K=32`, `EF=12` and changes only architecture after `routed` remained weak.","`two_stage_residual` is the next non-TopK comparison because it has prior real full-signal evidence and tests hierarchical residual allocation rather than support routing or TopK variants."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `two_stage_residual` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is still weak, pivot to another fundamentally different non-TopK direction in the same mainline band rather than reopening archived TopK-family comparisons."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0032.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery mode requires returning to the best known working family and making only a small stable parameter change. The recent lowrank_gated_residual sweeps showed that higher LR, added aux pressure, and larger EF all regress at K=128, so the clean remaining stability-oriented probe is to reduce only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 32 to 16 on the same winning signum recipe and test whether the family is over-parameterized at the anchor.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=128 with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=16`, holding architecture, optimizer, LR, aux, and batch settings fixed. This is a param-only recovery round on the best working configuration, aimed at checking whether a smaller residual dictionary improves stability or quality while also reducing cost.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash recovery mode by avoiding code edits and new architectures, and it stays on the strongest proven family with a single minor parameter adjustment. The choice also matches the remaining untested low-risk branch after the EF=48, LR, and aux probes all regressed.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash recovery mode forced a return to param-only search on the best working family, `lowrank_gated_residual`, with no code edits.","After regressions from higher LR, nonzero aux, and larger EF, the remaining low-risk probe is to reduce `EXPANSION_FACTOR` below the current EF=32 default at K=128.","This round also tests whether the winning family can retain anchor quality with lower dictionary capacity and better cost/stability characteristics."],"next_hypotheses":["If `EXPANSION_FACTOR=16` improves proxy FVU or holds quality with better runtime, promote it to full and then compare the same EF at K=64.","If EF=16 is flat or worse, keep EF=32 as the mainline default and continue crash recovery with another minor param-only probe such as `EXPANSION_FACTOR=4` rather than changing architecture.","If EF=16 improves throughput materially but loses only a little quality, consider it as a Pareto-strengthening cost point even if it does not beat the best K=128 FVU."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0035.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Ten no-improve rounds indicate the current fixed-per-sample-K search direction is fundamentally flawed, and recent pivots like `jumprelu` and `two_stage_residual` still stayed far behind the frontier. The next coherent architecture move is to change the sparsity mechanism itself: add `adaptive_budget_topk`, which keeps the same overall batch budget but allocates support dynamically across samples based on encoding difficulty instead of enforcing a rigid per-sample K. If hard examples need more active features and easy examples need fewer, this dynamic-budget routing could improve the quality frontier without changing the execution layer.","summary":"Add a new `adaptive_budget_topk` family under `sparsify/` and run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This is a genuine architecture pivot away from fixed per-sample TopK and tests whether dynamic batch-level support allocation is a better search direction than more tuning on the current mainline.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"adaptive_budget_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This round follows the mandatory architecture pivot and changes one core dimension only: the sparse allocation mechanism. The implementation is confined to `sparsify/`, registers cleanly with the existing config factory, and a local forward/backward smoke test passed with visibly non-uniform per-sample active counts under a shared batch budget.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"adaptive_budget_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added `adaptive_budget_topk`, a new sparse architecture that allocates a fixed batch-level feature budget dynamically across samples instead of enforcing the same K for every sample.","Registered `adaptive_budget_topk` in the existing architecture validation and factory paths under `sparsify/` only.","Local smoke test passed for `adaptive_budget_topk` forward/backward execution, and the encoded supports showed non-uniform per-sample active counts under batch execution."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adaptive_budget_topk` is competitive at K=128 proxy, keep the family alive and promote to full before local tuning.","If quality is promising but runtime is flagged as poor, follow with a narrow performance-oriented `code_fix` on the dynamic-budget path rather than discarding the family immediately.","If `adaptive_budget_topk` remains clearly behind, archive dynamic-budget routing and pivot to a different fundamentally different mechanism rather than returning to lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}

